300	11	Corsair launches new FRAME 5000D PC case	https://www.fudzilla.com/news/pc-hardware/61345-corsair-launches-new-frame-5000d-pc-case	<div class="K2FeedImage"><img alt="Corsair launches new FRAME 5000D PC case" src="https://www.fudzilla.com/media/k2/items/cache/864283c66c02a9edb442485d3663a729_S.jpg" /></div><div class="K2FeedIntroText"><p><br /><strong>Promises 30 percent more internal space&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Corsair has launched the newest entry in its FRAME PC case series, the modular mid-tower FRAME 5000D.&nbsp;</p> </div><div class="K2FeedFullText"> <p>As a successor to the popular FRAME 4000D PC case, <a href="https://www.corsair.com/us/en/p/pc-cases/CC-9011309-WW/frame-5000d-rs-argb-high-airflow-mid-tower-pc-case-cc-9011309-ww" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><em>the Corsair FRAME 5000D</em></a> promises over 30% more internal space, improved airflow design, and broader compatibility, including <strong>r</strong>everse connector motherboards like ASUS BTF, MSI Project Zero, and Gigabyte Project Stealth. It features Corsair's InfiniRail Fan Mounting System,&nbsp;GPU Anti-Sag Arm,&nbsp;RapidRoute 2.0 cable management, and other Corsair features. When it comes to cooling, it supports multiple 360mm radiators and even a top-mounted 420mm radiator, making it perfect for high-end builds.&nbsp;</p> <p>In case you are wondering, the Corsair 5000D measures 556x542x250mm, has two internal 3.5-inch and six 2.5-inch drive bays, has a tempered glass case window, supports up to 175mm tall CPU cooler, up to 450 long graphics card, and an ATX power supply.</p> <p>The FRAME 5000D is now available from Corsair’s website and authorized retailers, and comes in both black and white color options as well as bundled with standard Corsair RS140 fans or ARGB ones.</p> <p><img alt="corsair 5000d 1" height="500" src="https://www.fudzilla.com/images/stories/2025/July/corsair-5000d-1.jpg" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="1000" /></p> <p><img alt