Xh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAW4WeL8WEJfNPZng8Qc08x9BxikdO0vxbQEbtBupCWiz&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0C6WGP77V"><strong>Kindle case (fabric) for $24 (25 percent off with Prime)</strong></a>: If you want to protect your new ereader, you can grab this case while it's 25 percent off. Note that only the blue and pink versions are $24, the black and matcha versions are $2 more expensive.&nbsp;</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CN3XR57P&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=e155d041-da02-49ac-bb01-e64d7e7bed93&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Kindle+Colorsoft+for+%24180+%28%24100+off+with+Prime%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ04zWFI1N1A_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZTE1NWQwNDEtZGEwMi00OWFjLWJiMDEtZTY0ZDdlN2JlZDkzIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ04zWFI1N1AiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAbzLDlKnoRMUpD7Yff5wMF4xCf16G56L_0UwXg622sDO&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CN3XR57P"><strong>Kindle Colorsoft for $180 ($100 off with Prime)</strong></a>: Amazon didn’t introduce color to its ereader lineup until <a href="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/tablets/kindle-colorsoft-review-the-missing-link-in-amazons-ereader-lineup-131529685.html">early this year</a> — long after Kobo and Boox. The list price of $280 makes it more expensive than other color display ereaders, but this discount helps with that. We appreciate the fast page turns, pinch to zoom feature and auto-adjusting warm front light.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CZ9VFQ2P&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=e155d041-da02-49ac-bb01-e64d7e7bed93&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Kindle+Scribe+2+for+%24260+%28%24140+off+with+Prime%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ1o5VkZRMlA_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZTE1NWQwNDEtZGEwMi00OWFjLWJiMDEtZTY0ZDdlN2JlZDkzIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ1o5VkZRMlAiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAYlgTkZVH0NV27Qz_S_asCzzxqI-2jCQOekFrEb9_bzv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CZ9VFQ2P"><strong>Kindle Scribe 2 for $260 ($140 off with Prime)</strong></a>: If you want a Kindle that lets you write as well as read, this is the one to get. We gave the Kindle Scribe 2 <a href="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/tablets/kindle-scribe-2-review-in-progress-is-slightly-useful-ai-worth-the-extra-cash-140018638.html">a score of 86 in our review</a> and it’s our pick for the <a href="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/tablets/best-e-ink-tablet-130037939.html">best e-reader E Ink tablet</a>. It has a smooth reading and writing experience with low latency. It also lets you create multiple notebooks, add pages and change the templates easily.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CFPJYX7P&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=e155d041-da02-49ac-bb01-e64d7e7bed93&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Kindle+Paperwhite+for+%24125+%28%2435+off+with+Prime%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ0ZQSllYN1A_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZTE1NWQwNDEtZGEwMi00OWFjLWJiMDEtZTY0ZDdlN2JlZDkzIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ0ZQSllYN1AiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAfevdBEVFtB73MhiofnRYukeJ1-Iq1OPP-x5ojGS_WMG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CFPJYX7P"><strong>Kindle Paperwhite for $125 ($35 off with Prime)</strong></a>: The Paperwhite is an elevated version of the Kindle, with a larger, seven-inch, flush-front screen and an adjustable warm front light. A faster processor gives it quicker page turns than its predecessor and the device itself is waterproof.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CTMQTQNN&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=e155d041-da02-49ac-bb01-e64d7e7bed93&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Kindle+Paperwhite+Signature+Edition+for+%24150+%28%2450+off+with+Prime%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ1RNUVRRTk4_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZTE1NWQwNDEtZGEwMi00OWFjLWJiMDEtZTY0ZDdlN2JlZDkzIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ1RNUVRRTk4iLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAASrs2Rb5hAbR6zhMzX33s7uTY80Jlfvc6h9r7LMcQmNf&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CTMQTQNN"><strong>Kindle Paperwhite Signature Edition for $150 ($50 off with Prime)</strong></a>: The Signature Edition adds few more premium features to the Kindle Paperwhite with wireless charging, an auto-adjusting front light and more storage (32GB). We gave it an 85 in our review praising the premium build, remarkably clear text and fast page turns. We just wish the power button wasn’t on the bottom.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CNV9CQK8&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=e155d041-da02-49ac-bb01-e64d7e7bed93&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Kindle+Kids+for+%2495+%28%2435+off+with+Prime%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0FtYXpvbi1LaW5kbGUtS2lkcy9kcC9CMENOVjlDUUs4L3I_&amp;signature=AQAAAQiGZjIieTz1rfYWbnDmvBzYQmRdXJWS_7nJ1diGdsrm&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAmazon-Kindle-Kids%2Fdp%2FB0CNV9CQK8%2Fr"><strong>Kindle Kids for $95 ($35 off with Prime)</strong></a>: The Kindle Kids edition is the same hardware as the standard Kindle, but you get a few added perks that are fitting for younger users. To start, a case comes standard. The warranty is extended to two years. And the purchase price includes a six month subscription to Amazon Kids+ for thousands of kid-friendly ebooks and more.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CFPS7ZY9&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=e155d041-da02-49ac-bb01-e64d7e7bed93&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Kindle+Paperwhite+Kids+for+%24130+%28%2450+off+with+Prime%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ0ZQUzdaWTk_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZTE1NWQwNDEtZGEwMi00OWFjLWJiMDEtZTY0ZDdlN2JlZDkzIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ0ZQUzdaWTkiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAUNb9Fcc37K7MSCuBRir3fbVojYL5yko9uuj_Dwr27hM&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CFPS7ZY9"><strong>Kindle Paperwhite Kids for $130 ($50 off with Prime)</strong></a>: Again, the kids version is the same as the Paperwhite but with a cover, extended warranty and access to Amazon Kids+ for six months. Just remember to cancel at the end of the trial or keep it and pay $6 per month.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-deals-on-non-kindle-ereaders">Best Prime Day deals on non-Kindle ereaders</h2> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DSZWF122&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=e155d041-da02-49ac-bb01-e64d7e7bed93&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Boox+Palma+2+for+%24270+%28%2430+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdF_yhC-dPY_QfHB318ya3x_xQ1AYswcYRBLhI3oNY_E&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBOOX-Palma2-Fingerprint-Recognition-Microphones%2Fdp%2FB0DSZWF122%2F"><strong>Boox Palma 2 for $270 ($30 off)</strong></a>: This smartphone-shaped device <a href="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/tablets/best-ereader-130013808.html#:~:text=Amy%20Skorheim%20/%20Engadget-,Honorable%20mention,-Boox%20Palma">is a delight</a>. It’s built on Android and can run just about any app you can download from the Play Store — just don’t expect it to play video or graphics-intensive games. This is an E Ink screen, after all. But it’s perfect for reading books and running simple apps in a more eye-friendly format.</p>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/deals/last-chance-prime-day-deals-get-up-to-36-percent-off-kindles-and-ereaders-080957317.html?src=rss	2025-07-12 00:46:25	Amy Skorheim	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.479043
373	14	Amazon Prime Day deals on SSDs and external hard drives for the last day: Save on Samsung, Crucial, Sandisk and more	https://www.engadget.com/deals/amazon-prime-day-deals-on-ssds-and-external-hard-drives-for-the-last-day-save-on-samsung-crucial-sandisk-and-more-090355730.html?src=rss	<p>Solid-state drives (SSDs) come in many shapes, from thumbnail-sized microSD cards to larger external SSDs. But all classes of SSDs have one thing in common: at least one of the best brands is on sale right now for <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/amazon-prime-day-deals-are-already-live-through-july-11-here-are-our-top-picks-so-far-120028881.html">Amazon's Prime Day</a>. If you've been thinking about picking up some extra storage or trying to get the load times down on your Xbox or gaming PC, now's the time to get it done for cheap. Take a look at our curated list of the best SSD deals on Amazon this Prime Day.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-ssd-deals">Best Prime Day SSD deals</h2> \n<p>\n </p> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B07YD579WM&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Crucial+BX500+for+%2457+%2840+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeGQz3nBpWF0jQewZoRZNuU3YgBP5G9aPSLQkYtFUbIq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCrucial-BX500-NAND-2-5-Inch-Internal%2Fdp%2FB07YD579WM%2Fref%3Dpd_lpo_d_sccl_2%2F139-5238583-5507033"><strong>Crucial BX500 for $57 (40 percent off):</strong></a> The Crucial BX500 SSD is compatible with any computer that uses a 2.5-inch SATA drive — which is still plenty of them. For very cheap, you can get ahold of 1TB storage space and read speeds up to 540 MB/s, close to the very best possible for a SATA SSD.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0B7CKZGN6&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=WD_BLACK+SN850X+for+%24150+%2825+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfQHJaU6EY_yfV0T382XlNK-6yGpU79qvrrHGnnXJlBE&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0B7CKZGN6"><strong>WD_BLACK SN850X for $150 (25 percent off):</strong></a> Our current favorite Gen4 NVMe drive is on sale for Prime Day, making a read speed of over 7,000 MB/s more accessible than ever. In our tests, we found the 1TB SN850X significantly boosted our Windows operating speeds without adding much heat.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0F3BD1W6R&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=WD_BLACK+2TB+SN8100+for+%24180+%2844+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASrJatstJRDHh1lsJWBoaXxuwDgtq-389yuIkGBKacNw&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FWD_BLACK-SN8100-Internal-Solid-State%2Fdp%2FB0F3BD1W6R"><strong>WD_BLACK 2TB SN8100 for $180 (44 percent off):</strong></a> If you frequently need read and write speeds measured in kilobytes instead of megabytes, the WD_BLACK SN8100 is for you. This internal SSD easily breaches 1400 KB/s, and is especially suited for gaming or AI work.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D7MLB76V&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=WD+Blue+SN5000+for+%24200+%2833+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWXgd82zkGqXOVR_jGdNZ_WoDUdFbE-ByLmv8dJSDnxq&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D7MLB76V"><strong>WD Blue SN5000 for $200 (33 percent off):</strong></a> Here's a great deal on an internal SSD with 4TB capacity and compatibility with the fast-performing NVMe protocol. Western Digital, the same brand behind the WD_BLACK (see above) claims the Blue model can hit read speeds of 5,500 MB/s.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CGKPPZY9&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Lexar+1TB+NM790+for+%2467+%2829+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0xleGFyLUhlYXRzaW5rLUludGVybmFsLUNvbXBhdGlibGUtTE5NNzkwWDAwMVQtUk45TlUvZHAvQjBDR0tQUFpZOS8_&amp;signature=AQAAAW5lsWcR5Mv3DTZpWO7vtCqz2Y8WsnF5D4IXh4FWAsRH&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLexar-Heatsink-Internal-Compatible-LNM790X001T-RN9NU%2Fdp%2FB0CGKPPZY9%2F"><strong>Lexar 1TB NM790 for $67 (29 percent off):</strong></a> The NM790 is a single-sided SSD that can post sequential read speeds of 7400 MB/s. The one-sided design means it stays cooler for longer, and this 1TB deal includes a heatsink. It's a great budget alternative to the also single-sided Samsung 990 Pro (see below).</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0C5YS3QY4&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sabrent+Rocket+2230+for+%24150+%2815+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWQluq3rSLtholiX2V00T9002tFUZSa6h85fTy1d1Qzj&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0C5YS3QY4"><strong>Sabrent Rocket 2230 for $150 (15 percent off):</strong></a> The Sabrent Rocket 2230 is a thumbnail-sized NVMe card that we found to be perfect for the M.2 slot on a Steam Deck. Thanks to this deal, you can save a lot by buying a lower-end Steam Deck and upgrading it with one of these.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B07D7Q41PM&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+Fit+Plus+for+%2423+%2834+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwN0Q3UTQxUE0_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiODI4ZTdjZTctZTkzMS00YmI2LWFjNWMtYzJiOTg2NGIzNDgxIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwN0Q3UTQxUE0iLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAV-73WGchaGdlPvA7M2lCgCQyPtg4smUoBQ4yN-AlySI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07D7Q41PM"><strong>Samsung Fit Plus for $23 (34 percent off):</strong></a> The Fit Plus is our favorite thumb drive, and it's not close. Running on USB 3.1 with transfer speeds between 300 and 400 MB/s, it even comes with a keychain hook. The current deal takes 34 percent off an already cheap product.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B08QBJ2YMG&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+870+EVO+for+%2476+%2824+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVlKYnMCJAujAZR2Bl1CCXd-T_1WkJkx2keOkZ4FKYIu&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB08QBJ2YMG"><strong>Samsung 870 EVO for $76 (24 percent off):</strong></a> The 870 EVO is a great budget choice for general users, who are likely to get a speed boost on any PC activity once it's installed. At 560 MB/s of maximum reading speed, it's not for hardcore gamers, but everyday users should see real benefits.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DHLFWBQ1&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+990+EVO+Plus+1TB+for+%2466+%2837+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdEmKArVg-d5j7K9_0gkIZJJJXRk-v8nBCh5MwWmTJ9V&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Technology-Intelligent-Turbowrite-MZ-V9S1T0B%2Fdp%2FB0DHLFWBQ1"><strong>Samsung 990 EVO Plus 1TB for $66 (37 percent off):</strong></a> Samsung's EVO line never rests on its laurels. The 990 EVO was already fast, but the 990 EVO Plus doubled its speeds less than a year later. Currently, all three sizes are on sale for lowest-ever prices.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BHJDY57J&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+990+Pro+for+%24150+%2829+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAY0FppqZ_4APgmpJ2hV9WIO2A1QX_3rxI3yLz6YW56MV&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BHJDY57J"><strong>Samsung 990 Pro for $150 (29 percent off):</strong></a> The whole Samsung Pro line of SSDs is excellent for gamers, with PS5s in particular seeming to run much faster with one installed. The 990 Pro can reach read speeds of up to 1,400 KB/s — and yes, that's kilobytes, not megabytes.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DX2FN49V&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+9100+Pro+for+%24220+%2831+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXjGHlqo1yi5zGSPjltMEmSdiD6-dDkumA0NTzGIazkd&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0DX2FN49V"><strong>Samsung 9100 Pro for $220 (31 percent off):</strong></a> Samsung's first NVMe SSD dropped earlier this year, and currently, they're still a bit faster than most people can use. However, if you want to get a jump on the next console generation with 14,800 MB/s sequential reading speed, this deal is your opportunity.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0F43Z6NXL&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Kingston+Fury+Renegade+for+%24420+%2833+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAY7VNabc4SX6zfsbSrcQPuOJu_HDz3EXY74Hhg9RTI94&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0F43Z6NXL"><strong>Kingston Fury Renegade for $420 (33 percent off):</strong></a> Although it sounds like a Jamaican kung fu movie we'd watch the hell out of, the Kingston Fury Renegade is actually a 5th-gen NVMe SSD that can reach hardcore read speeds of up to 14,800 MB/s. It's expensive, but Prime Day discounts knock off 33 percent.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09Q2NCFS7&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Corsair+MP600+Pro+LPX+2+TB+for+%24160+%2820+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARsY8CaSc2htvIO01Idm8CXQqoBlAILy0NgF5LGbnyiI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCorsair-MP600-NVMe-PCIe-Gen4%2Fdp%2FB09Q2NCFS7"><strong>Corsair MP600 Pro LPX 2 TB for $160 (20 percent off):</strong></a> Earlier this year, we named the Corsair MP600 Pro LPX as the top SSD for PS5, partly due to its affordability. It's even more affordable now, and the low price even includes a heatsink.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B08Z33H1C3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Acer+FA100+1TB+for+%2451+%2815+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0FjZXItRkExMDAtSW50ZXJmYWNlLUludGVybmFsLVRlY2hub2xvZ3kvZHAvQjA4WjMzSDFDMy8_&amp;signature=AQAAAesvHb1JbbVg9mjLJs7AqD4gsAJSdqhCZqwKGJYq7OVT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAcer-FA100-Interface-Internal-Technology%2Fdp%2FB08Z33H1C3%2F"><strong>Acer FA100 1TB for $51 (15 percent off):</strong></a> The Acer FA100 isn't the fastest SSD, but it is at least competitive, and may be one of the cheapest ways to harness the considerable power of NVMe 3.0. Only the 1TB version is marked down for Prime Day.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BJZLF2FW&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=KingSpec+512GB+for+%2425+%2815+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0tpbmdTcGVjLUludGVybmFsLURyaXZlcy1Db21wYXRpYmxlLURlc2t0b3AvZHAvQjBCSlpMRjJGVy8_&amp;signature=AQAAARttWGe4wrSSnhqZ-KujunQp8tUUSE_UMA2vZBVAxswB&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FKingSpec-Internal-Drives-Compatible-Desktop%2Fdp%2FB0BJZLF2FW%2F"><strong>KingSpec 512GB for $25 (15 percent off):</strong></a> KingSpec is a Chinese manufacturer that's been quietly making some of the best cheap SSDs for years now. Their 512GB internal SSD runs SATA III and can reach 550 MB/s read speeds — not the most impressive, but amazing for the price.</p></li> \n</ul> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-portable-ssd-deals">Best Prime Day portable SSD deals</h2> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0874Y5XFG&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+T7+for+%24114+%2839+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAevqfW5TCLRRySTiM1ETM_ZjRfmwhSZIPTjHcRS7yjqy&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0874Y5XFG"><strong>Samsung T7 for $114 (39 percent off):</strong></a> The T7 spent a long time as our reigning champion portable SSD, and it's still an amazing deal — being technically outdated means record-low prices on hardware that's more than fast enough for a Steam Deck or Switch.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CHFS9K14&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+T9+for+%24170+%2843+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZYeqYqAqn4-jTt7FHsdgU4fAAF2q4mlQOLx6rkRPKiP&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CHFS9K14"><strong>Samsung T9 for $170 (43 percent off):</strong></a> We once named the Samsung T7 as our favorite portable SSD, but the T9 handily outdoes it, nearly doubling data transfer speeds. It's marked down 43 percent from now until the end of Prime Day on the 11th.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B08GTYFC37&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=SanDisk+1TB+Extreme+for+%2478+%2840+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAf4NqEHxg6MKSKm71NZvLoWkCo547cbiG98UhewLWl6B&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSanDisk-1TB-Extreme-Portable-SDSSDE61-1T00-G25%2Fdp%2FB08GTYFC37%2Fref%3Dsr_1_3%3Fs%3Dpc"><strong>SanDisk 1TB Extreme for $78 (40 percent off):</strong></a> SanDisk designed the Extreme for portability, and it shows — this is an almost indestructible SSD you can keep in just about any bag or pocket. It's also reasonably fast, though it only works with USB-C. This 1TB deal knocks off 40 percent of the price.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B08HN37XC1&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=SanDisk+2TB+Extreme+for+%24120+%2843+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NhbkRpc2stMlRCLUV4dHJlbWUtUG9ydGFibGUtU0RTU0RFNjEtMlQwMC1HMjUvZHAvQjA4SE4zN1hDMS8_&amp;signature=AQAAAfyvpKta-uPUSlcQsMYLuJ14po8iJDLs4Z17wWK_mIrC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSanDisk-2TB-Extreme-Portable-SDSSDE61-2T00-G25%2Fdp%2FB08HN37XC1%2F"><strong>SanDisk 2TB Extreme for $120 (43 percent off):</strong></a> The 2TB version of the SanDisk Extreme is on sale for 43 percent off, saving you $90 on 1,050 MB/s of read speed.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B08RX3343D&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=SanDisk+4TB+Extreme+PRO+for+%24270+%2832+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NhbkRpc2stNFRCLUV4dHJlbWUtUG9ydGFibGUtU0RTU0RFODEtNFQwMC1HMjUvZHAvQjA4UlgzMzQzRC8_&amp;signature=AQAAASyBMCvbSkS-8g6GAfCAxcLzR12ilOwismn9MT5Ap1gn&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSanDisk-4TB-Extreme-Portable-SDSSDE81-4T00-G25%2Fdp%2FB08RX3343D%2F"><strong>SanDisk 4TB Extreme PRO for $270 (32 percent off):</strong></a> This deal doubles not only the storage space of the 2TB Extreme above, but also its read and write speeds, with each hovering around 2000 MB/s. It's a very cheap way to get your hands on a USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 drive.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0C9WKGXHD&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Crucial+X9+Pro+1TB+for+%2475+%2817+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAb9y9YonyA7PEn05lkh0WNJbDfxfpav35MnCPL5xUncp&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0C9WKGXHD"><strong>Crucial X9 Pro 1TB for $75 (17 percent off):</strong></a> As a Gen 2 USB drive, the Crucial X9 Pro loses out to some newer competitors on speed — but it's much cheaper, and far more compatible with everyday personal computers. The 1TB model is on sale at 17 percent off its normal price.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0C9WHSZZN&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Crucial+X9+Pro+2TB+for+%24120+%2833+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAV003Lp7TYS2FDsEwOfw_Hgricl7e-IRbVEZNBuvvYN5&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0C9WHSZZN"><strong>Crucial X9 Pro 2TB for $120 (33 percent off):</strong></a> The Crucial X9 Pro with 2TB storage space is marked down 33 percent for Prime Day.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0F3377JBN&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Crucial+X10+1TB+for+%2482+%2824+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQSfVkWyzBCG2NXjCn9ghZ0iqZnzzvuKLakWcl-dCzNe&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0F3377JBN"><strong>Crucial X10 1TB for $82 (24 percent off):</strong></a> The Crucial X10 is a portable SSD for power users, only working at full strength on devices that support the latest version of USB 3.2. If that's what your build needs, you're not likely to see it much cheaper than this.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0F332MNX7&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Crucial+X10+2TB+for+%24135+%2818+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZ_ZdVV88zB-N50gHeFvS5NwHF39SMlrrYOvX_Br5ddd&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0F332MNX7"><strong>Crucial X10 2TB for $135 (18 percent off):</strong></a> A 2TB version of the X10 is almost 20 percent off right now.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0C9WGS6MC&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Crucial+X10+Pro+2TB+for+%24150+%2828+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQFK946dMbwLupm9Cx1N32NrmMbGN53m2BgBWfHl6Oxi&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0C9WGS6MC"><strong>Crucial X10 Pro 2TB for $150 (28 percent off):</strong></a> The Crucial X10 Pro is perfect for a fairly small range of users. If your PC build currently works with USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 but isn't yet handling USB4 or Thunderbolt, you won't find a faster portable SSD for your needs.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CCQB7BN7&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Kingston+XS1000+for+%2480+%2815+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ0NRQjdCTjc_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiODI4ZTdjZTctZTkzMS00YmI2LWFjNWMtYzJiOTg2NGIzNDgxIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ0NRQjdCTjciLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAUHuw6T9kg9Wya-QwTlABhDIVlDzfoxx5Ml_vF-0ubnb&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CCQB7BN7"><strong>Kingston XS1000 for $80 (15 percent off):</strong></a> We named the Kingston XS1000 the second-best portable SSD in our current roundup, so it's great to see it going for 15 percent off today. It's almost as fast as the Crucial X9 Pro, just not quite as tough.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D4B5YQ54&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=ADATA+SE920+for+%24142+%285+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0FEQVRBLVNFOTIwLVBvcnRhYmxlLUV4dGVybmFsLUNvbXBhdGlibGUvZHAvQjBENEI1WVE1NC8_&amp;signature=AQAAAQLlH_6XjqqvJE1MpkxUi4PwuXl1opF7N-_VlzWVxazv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FADATA-SE920-Portable-External-Compatible%2Fdp%2FB0D4B5YQ54%2F"><strong>ADATA SE920 for $142 (5 percent off):</strong></a> The piddly 5 percent off is disappointing, but there's nothing disappointing about the ADATA SE920 itself. This is the ideal model for anyone regularly making huge downloads. The SE920's maximum read speed of 3,800 MB/s would be impressive for a full-size SSD, but it's fully portable, weighing less than half a pound.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DHKZGB5M&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Garmese+1TB+Portable+SSD+for+%2464+%2820+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0dBUk1FU0UtRXh0ZXJuYWwtU1NELVBvcnRhYmxlLUNvbnNvbGUvZHAvQjBESEtaR0I1TS8_&amp;signature=AQAAAQNYukd0JFon-tNh-LH8OZqH_4Lkq6-2PIq7N01fmig2&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGARMESE-External-SSD-Portable-Console%2Fdp%2FB0DHKZGB5M%2F"><strong>Garmese 1TB Portable SSD for $64 (20 percent off):</strong></a> This portable SSD uses USB3.2 to achieve read speeds of around 1000 MB/s, which is very impressive for a device not much larger than a flash drive. While it downloads fast, it's not fantastic for transferring multiple files at a time.</p></li> \n</ul> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-microsd-card-deals">Best Prime Day microSD card deals</h2> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D9MVKMY4&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Lexar+Professional+Silver+Plus+for+%2438+%2848+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRDlNVktNWTQ_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiODI4ZTdjZTctZTkzMS00YmI2LWFjNWMtYzJiOTg2NGIzNDgxIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRDlNVktNWTQiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAARCYeG2GRXa2IpgYOTVWIUd_9DQIT82LGG__yy7bVXGS&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D9MVKMY4"><strong>Lexar Professional Silver Plus for $38 (48 percent off):</strong></a> Our tests showed this to be the fastest microSD card on the market, beating out the whole Samsung line. Not only is it fast enough to download and upload 4K files without trying your patience, it's also waterproof, cheap and squeezes in both USB-A and USB-C ports.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CQX2B25W&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Lexar+E-Series+for+%2431+%2815+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXszqsNQzhK4CEJoivPWMTW0FR3AqDORMAmLxYrxdLL9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLexar-Micro-microSDXC-Memory-Adapter%2Fdp%2FB0CQX2B25W%2F"><strong>Lexar E-Series for $31 (15 percent off):</strong></a> While the Silver Plus beats it out, the Lexar E-Series remains more than fast enough for 4K video, and is sufficiently rugged to fit in your adventure camera. This deal includes a five-pack of microSD cards, working out to about six dollars per 64GB of storage.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0C1PT9XXS&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+Pro+Plus+for+%2417+%2835+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQzFQVDlYWFM_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiODI4ZTdjZTctZTkzMS00YmI2LWFjNWMtYzJiOTg2NGIzNDgxIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQzFQVDlYWFMiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAa_A0O-Snat_xxuh20BREel7xIL6iyeYJVOO_O582Dub&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0C1PT9XXS"><strong>Samsung Pro Plus for $17 (35 percent off):</strong></a> The Samsung Pro Plus is a great microSD card for most needs, so if it's cheaper than the Lexar option, go for it. We've found that it's particularly good in handheld game systems. Just make sure to get the version rated for 180 MB/s, nothing less (it should say on the package).</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0B7NV73PJ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=SanDisk+Ultra+256GB+microSDXC+for+%2417+%2835+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUk8erdJwhDeHSx__O5mwg90UfjqPRsD75kPUgaqqwSh&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSanDisk-256GB-microSDXC-Memory-Adapter%2Fdp%2FB0B7NV73PJ%2F"><strong>SanDisk Ultra 256GB microSDXC for $17 (35 percent off):</strong></a> If you're still rocking the Switch 1 (thanks, Target) and want a cheap storage expander, this deal on a SanDisk 256GB microSD card is for you. It's going for $17 right now, far less than most of the games you're likely to store on it.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09B1GXM16&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+Evo+Select+for+%2422+%2827+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAb9M0ST7YRFnq88HcAg2ViVu9URME07Ed64-XCr9jYHG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-microSDXC-Expanded-MB-ME256KA-AM%2Fdp%2FB09B1GXM16"><strong>Samsung Evo Select for $22 (27 percent off):</strong></a> This one's by far the best option if you're after a cheap microSD card — we've seen it on sale for less than $25 more than once. It's a bit too slow for cameras, but fine for any kind of undemanding passive storage.</p></li> \n</ul> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-external-hard-drive-deals">Best Prime Day external hard drive deals</h2> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B07CRG94G3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Seagate+Portable+for+%2465+%2819+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQmSfWGNzA6hPm4eXgCbxwHrqfWHtyOEIXKdaLBOF7LU&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07CRG94G3"><strong>Seagate Portable for $65 (19 percent off):</strong></a> All the Seagate hard drives we've used are refreshingly good at combining thin, light hardware with consistent speeds, and the Portable is no exception. At 4TB, this is a great deal on an external HDD with no tradeoffs.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CH87VY5B&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Seagate+Game+Drive+for+%2476+%2816+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARBqq7qLuYL2QbbfebVbg-MRCHcKpCqmt2Q2Vb9ES435&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CH87VY5B"><strong>Seagate Game Drive for $76 (16 percent off):</strong></a> Seagate's Game Drive is a prime choice for adding extra space to a PS5 or Xbox Series X. Formerly overpriced, it's now dropped down to $90 for 2 TB, and that's before Prime Day makes it even cheaper.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D1YHH6XJ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=WD+My+Passport+for+%24140+%2824+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASD9aSafINPmuMa1ZKPFiFKwyhhsqMdbxt-5aogBK_xr&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D1YHH6XJ"><strong>WD My Passport for $140 (24 percent off):</strong></a> The Western Digital My Passport line is ancient by computer hardware standards, but it's been updated as far as USB 3.0 and 3.1, and remains one of the cheaper options for a 6 TB hard drive. This version includes automatic backup software.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D3GW9R4G&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=WD+Elements+6TB+for+%24130+%2826+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUVMFjg8OizcfXZcIv-IIrNH4qzxERfCUGYhFlpQ61nv&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D3GW9R4G"><strong>WD Elements 6TB for $130 (26 percent off):</strong></a> The Elements HDD from Western Digital has gotten consistently positive feedback from our staff over the years, and as an older model, it's now wildly cheap for 6 TB of storage. It's compatible with both PC and Mac out of the box.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B08KTRBHP1&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=WD+Elements+18TB+for+%24308+%2842+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0VsZW1lbnRzLURlc2t0b3AtRHJpdmUtQ29tcGF0aWJsZS1XREJXTEcwMTgwSEJLLU5FU04vZHAvQjA4S1RSQkhQMS8_&amp;signature=AQAAATDiafRSahJ5INdgXQEUK718qFe4i1rV4T4egqfyObea&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FElements-Desktop-Drive-Compatible-WDBWLG0180HBK-NESN%2Fdp%2FB08KTRBHP1%2F"><strong>WD Elements 18TB for $308 (42 percent off):</strong></a> If you need a lot more storage, WD has also heavily discounted the 18TB version of the elements, slicing well over $200 off the price.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D3GXP8NB&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=WD_BLACK+P10+Game+Drive+for+%24155+%2818+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbEkiiQRDcX5-kJlumcyeMlv4JJiEu3KDUZKCJoNDx-f&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D3GXP8NB"><strong>WD_BLACK P10 Game Drive for $155 (18 percent off):</strong></a> We're big fans of the WD_BLACK SSD, and the gaming-focused external P10 is a worthy companion. It comes with 6 TB of storage for your PC, PS5, or Xbox gaming library.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B091FSXH5V&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=UnionSine+50&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1VuaW9uU2luZS1Qb3J0YWJsZS1FeHRlcm5hbC1TdG9yYWdlLUNvbXBhdGlibGUvZHAvQjA5MUZTWEg1Vi8_&amp;signature=AQAAAU4Si-j8-Q76ldynxgCYORo_VphZ0vgpOlNODOomZpJI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FUnionSine-Portable-External-Storage-Compatible%2Fdp%2FB091FSXH5V%2F"><strong>UnionSine 50</strong></a><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B091FSXH5V&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=828e7ce7-e931-4bb6-ac5c-c2b9864b3481&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=0GB+External+Hard+Drive+for+%2427+%2819+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1VuaW9uU2luZS1Qb3J0YWJsZS1FeHRlcm5hbC1TdG9yYWdlLUNvbXBhdGlibGUvZHAvQjA5MUZTWEg1Vi8_&amp;signature=AQAAAU4Si-j8-Q76ldynxgCYORo_VphZ0vgpOlNODOomZpJI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FUnionSine-Portable-External-Storage-Compatible%2Fdp%2FB091FSXH5V%2F"><strong>0GB External Hard Drive for $27 (19 percent off):</strong></a> UnionSine's HDD is fast and USB3 compatible. Despite how thin and light it is, we've found it remarkably hard to damage. 500GB may be a bit tight with the size of files these days, but at this price, you could just buy two of them.</p></li> \n</ul>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/deals/amazon-prime-day-deals-on-ssds-and-external-hard-drives-for-the-last-day-save-on-samsung-crucial-sandisk-and-more-090355730.html?src=rss	2025-07-12 00:30:37	Sam Chapman	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.480025
374	14	The best Prime Day speaker deals: Last chance to get up to 47 percent off on JBL, Bose, Sonos and others	https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-best-prime-day-speaker-deals-last-chance-to-get-up-to-47-percent-off-on-jbl-bose-sonos-and-others-085948445.html?src=rss	<p>July's <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/amazon-prime-day-deals-are-already-live-through-july-11-here-are-our-top-picks-so-far-120028881.html">Prime Day sale</a> is here, which means Amazon is offering sharp discounts on some of the best speakers money can buy. Whether you're after a <a href="https://www.engadget.com/audio/speakers/best-portable-bluetooth-speakers-133004551.html">portable bluetooth speaker</a>, a <a href="https://www.engadget.com/audio/speakers/best-soundbars-143041791.html">compact yet powerful soundbar</a> or a <a href="https://www.engadget.com/audio/speakers/best-smart-speakers-151515264.html">smart speaker</a> to help around the house, something probably just dropped into your price range. Our audiophiles have combed through the sales and put together a list of discounted speakers that stand out from the herd, including top brands like Beats, Marshall, Bose and Sonos. So if you're sick of missing important dialogue in your shows, or you want to listen to music like it's live, check out the list below.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-bluetooth-speaker-deals">Best Prime Day Bluetooth speaker deals</h2> \n<p>Our portable bluetooth speaker picks are some of the best all-around mobile music devices to ever hit the shelves: smaller and lighter than a boombox, better audio than an iPod, and way easier in the long run than learning to play guitar. We've sifted through Prime Day offerings to find the best portable speakers in all shapes and sizes.</p> <span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>\n<p>\n </p> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DGJ5F42Q&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Beats+Pill+for+%2498+%2835+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2dwL2F3L2QvQjBER0o1RjQyUS8_&amp;signature=AQAAAeMaDvxz9-IsJa1H8FBmryDaGznKhyR-U9bwSCFKwnZo&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Faw%2Fd%2FB0DGJ5F42Q%2F"><strong>Beats Pill for $98 (35 percent off):</strong></a> The Beats Pill is one of the few portable bluetooth speakers we liked enough to give it a <a href="https://www.engadget.com/beats-pill-review-a-revival-worth-the-wait-160056269.html">full review</a>. Those of you who love the classic Beats bluetooth speakers will be happy to know they're back in fine form. Nobody can beat the Pill for bass, and its sound is crisp and lossless at almost any frequency and volume. For some reason, only the Kim Kardashian branded version is on sale, but it's the exact same speaker.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CQ53RVTW&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Soundcore+Boom+2+for+%2490+%2836+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcBXgV1tn6q157aT1GygP0luImOjLmayaaMtHLYjjhUe&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSoundcore-Subwoofer-Waterproof-Floatable-Bluetooth%2Fdp%2FB0CQ53RVTW%2F"><strong>Soundcore Boom 2 for $90 (36 percent off):</strong></a> This lightweight but powerful indoor/outdoor speaker is highly customizable, with simple controls to balance for pounding bass or clear high-frequency audio. It's great at filling an area with an even proportion of sound. $90 is close to a record-low price.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CDJWTWMB&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Soundcore+Motion+300+for+%2453+%2834+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWUmP7zjwZgBw3IZ-IDI6-CHL6lAvs0mV87UcMXNGjLr&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSoundcore-Bluetooth-SmartTune-Technology-Waterproof%2Fdp%2FB0CDJWTWMB"><strong>Soundcore Motion 300 for $53 (34 percent off):</strong></a> The Motion 300 is that rare portable speaker that outperforms at both high and low frequencies. Its upper range goes into 40 kHz, while its bass can deliver bone-shaking thumps even outdoors. All that in 1.7 pounds with 13 hours of battery life — and it's even partially waterproof.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B07P39MLKH&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Anker+Soundcore+Motion%2B+for+%2475+%2824+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0Fua2VyLVNvdW5kY29yZS1CbHVldG9vdGgtQ3VzdG9taXphYmxlLVdhdGVycHJvb2YvZHAvQjA3UDM5TUxLSC8_&amp;signature=AQAAAUU0jgSK2HFS6MfXQLKEPKzsTzRmIG4VVBl1C0c04g1_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAnker-Soundcore-Bluetooth-Customizable-Waterproof%2Fdp%2FB07P39MLKH%2F"><strong>Anker Soundcore Motion+ for $75 (24 percent off):</strong></a> Tough, sturdy construction makes this speaker an excellent choice for home bluetooth. Its battery lasts for 12 hours in the wild, and it always sounds great, but it's a bit heavy for pedaling through the park. There's also an option for wired connections, and it even works as a backup soundbar.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B01MTB55WH&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Anker+Soundcore+2+for+%2428+%2838+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAaiGnjQAlXwCYEsi7hlisJKFxWM_-mgaxKiByJ5oimlV&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB01MTB55WH"><strong>Anker Soundcore 2 for $28 (38 percent off):</strong></a> The Soundcore 2 is an older bluetooth speaker, but it holds up — fully waterproof, with 24 hours of battery life and bass you can hear on the other side of a pool. It's on sale for less than $30.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DB1753RZ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Soundcore+Select+4+for+%2419+%2846+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NvdW5kY29yZS1CbHVldG9vdGgtV2F0ZXJwcm9vZi1EdXN0cHJvb2YtRWxlY3Ryb25pY3MvZHAvQjBEQjE3NTNSWi8_&amp;signature=AQAAAbMIDW-h1A8VfIMTYhuAHHSpB1WYRTpnHPvc9we8Y5WU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSoundcore-Bluetooth-Waterproof-Dustproof-Electronics%2Fdp%2FB0DB1753RZ%2F"><strong>Soundcore Select 4 for $19 (46 percent off):</strong></a> This 9.3-ounce speaker is a massive improvement over built-in smartphone audio. It can fill a room at a decent range of frequencies, and works well in room-sized outdoor spaces — plus, with IP67 waterproofing, it can survive a dip in the pool. It's currently almost half off.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BYCBRXVM&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=UE+Everboom+for+%24190+%2830+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAapxHYvIhP851do6wPBfmUE2CzPIi_HCSdcQBDIoNcYa&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BYCBRXVM"><strong>UE Everboom for $190 (30 percent off):</strong></a> If you want something stronger than the Wonderboom but the Hyperboom isn't portable enough, the Everboom is a great middle ground. Its ideal range is a little narrow, but it makes up for that with 360-degree sound and extreme durability (i.e. so waterproof it literally floats).</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B07CVPZJTV&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=JBL+Xtreme+2+for+%24150+%2817+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfTlzaMSqe92z_NKNq1Zv9DQDp4j61wpHGB4JzmUmzTF&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FJBL-Waterproof-portable-Bluetooth-speaker%2Fdp%2FB07CVPZJTV%2F"><strong>JBL Xtreme 2 for $150 (17 percent off):</strong></a> The Xtreme 2 is an older model, dating back to 2018 — but as they say on the internet, it checks out. With a maximum output of 40 watts, it's actually more powerful than the Xtreme 4. Even better, this deal includes a pair of speakers that can work together through JBL connect+.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CQ53RVTW&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=JBL+Boombox+3+for+%24400+%2820+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcBXgV1tn6q157aT1GygP0luImOjLmayaaMtHLYjjhUe&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSoundcore-Subwoofer-Waterproof-Floatable-Bluetooth%2Fdp%2FB0CQ53RVTW%2F"><strong>JBL Boombox 3 for $400 (20 percent off):</strong></a> The JBL Boombox 3 is a great choice for getting a bit louder. It's tough, portable and ready to go right out of the box, although it would be a little overpriced without this Prime Day deal.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BQPVNJFN&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=JBL+Pulse+5+for+%24197+%2821+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0pCTC1QdWxzZS1Qb3J0YWJsZS1CbHVldG9vdGgtRGF6emxpbmcvZHAvQjBCUVBWTkpGTi8_&amp;signature=AQAAAWeaT4VOtDJVou1jqNMDdHhHwVE_XMyBrt2t3inMSVSO&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FJBL-Pulse-Portable-Bluetooth-Dazzling%2Fdp%2FB0BQPVNJFN%2F"><strong>JBL Pulse 5 for $197 (21 percent off):</strong></a> The Pulse 5 is JBL's latest and greatest party speaker, throwing out 360-degree light bursts that sync up to the music. There's substance behind the flash, too, with speakers designed around the bass frequencies and 12 hours of battery life.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CTP56C5R&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=JBL+Clip+5+for+%2460+%2825+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAens4RRJCbFEYoV7TzfA-ITCUopSfBRchdyjsblrsSfz&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FJBL-Clip-Ultra-Portable-Waterproof-Integrated%2Fdp%2FB0CTP56C5R"><strong>JBL Clip 5 for $60 (25 percent off):</strong></a> The JBL Clip 5 is a traveling speaker, coming with a carabiner-friendly design, 15 hours of battery life, and IP67-rated waterproofing and dustproofing. It's not exactly powerful, but it's way better than a phone speaker for driving, trekking or camping.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D6W8X6L2&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Bose+SoundLink+Flex+2nd+Gen+for+%2499+%2834+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATOCiexRZcjuSG3RlZPaIG10qiLHWYUqlPHtOvyIfuVo&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D6W8X6L2"><strong>Bose SoundLink Flex 2nd Gen for $99 (34 percent off):</strong></a> This mini speaker from Bose is one of our favorites on the list for hands-free phone calls. It supports both Google Assistant and Siri and runs up to 12 hours on one charge, all while being smaller than a clutch purse. It also kills as a portable music player, though the sound doesn't stretch far enough to fill a room.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B08VLD15ZL&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Bose+Soundlink+Revolve%2B+Series+II+for+%24179+%2840+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVbJeDFY15GOD-pUdvGqZaUBF-gUAGVTy9UZzxCxCCKZ&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB08VLD15ZL"><strong>Bose Soundlink Revolve+ Series II for $179 (40 percent off):</strong></a> The Revolve series was Bose's first line of 360-degree outdoor speakers, and they're still a strong choice today. The Revolve+ weighs about two pounds and can run for 17 hours without recharging.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CVLD42PD&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Bose+Soundlink+Max+for+%24299+%2825+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYYEHQlQZVD8VQ2PXt-OFzUFo8A5s7CshltVfJL42d7N&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CVLD42PD"><strong>Bose Soundlink Max for $299 (25 percent off):</strong></a> Bose's Soundlink Max marries a classic carrying-case design with audio that sounds like it's coming from a much bigger unit. It comes with a 20-hour battery and IP67-rated protection against the elements.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09XXW54QG&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Marshall+Emberton+II+for+%2495+%2847+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAc2AVxO7aaThONQSF69fCdqPE9Zy0DXztrOb-yw48EKJ&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09XXW54QG"><strong>Marshall Emberton II for $95 (47 percent off):</strong></a> Marshall has been making audio equipment for more than 60 years, and still has a thing or two to teach the young'ns. The Emberton II looks like a classic amp, but weighs a quarter of a pound and provides balanced sound for more than 30 hours per charge.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BC27MM5Z&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Marshall+Acton+III+for+%24200+%2833+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAR6BbNgEElZMcbyTNdp1EFbRpgVuY2Msy-ZRrF5e9GT0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMarshall-Acton-Bluetooth-Speaker-Black%2Fdp%2FB0BC27MM5Z%2F"><strong>Marshall Acton III for $200 (33 percent off):</strong></a> All right, so a six-pound speaker isn't exactly portable — but if you can stand lugging it around, the Acton III can be a highly versatile device. From music to outdoor parties to pulling double duty as a soundbar, this is a low-setup, low-overhead option for nearly all audio tasks.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CXKSCY1G&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sony+Ult+Field+1+for+%2488+%2832+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAb9gy7Ck5fjgQge7DiCuMWBgMSdOFa1RbXLPCBVx-dHY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-Bluetooth-Waterproof-Shockproof-Detachable%2Fdp%2FB0CXKSCY1G%2F"><strong>Sony Ult Field 1 for $88 (32 percent off):</strong></a> The Ult Field line is Sony's most bass-heavy sound tech yet, but it's also designed to move — waterproofing, a detachable strap and 12-hour battery life make it a good fit for any situation. It works just as well standing up or lying on its side.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B08FDPW8KR&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Ortizan+X10+for+%2430+%2841+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL09ydGl6YW4tUG9ydGFibGUtQmx1ZXRvb3RoLVdhdGVycHJvb2YtV2lyZWxlc3MvZHAvQjA4RkRQVzhLUi8_&amp;signature=AQAAAaG2VQuOzgvY5OriGZkqUw4KhPlcC4iETQltZce3Qs3M&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FOrtizan-Portable-Bluetooth-Waterproof-Wireless%2Fdp%2FB08FDPW8KR%2F"><strong>Ortizan X10 for $30 (41 percent off):</strong></a> Ortizan is a newer brand from China, but we like what we've seen from them so far. The X10 is the size of the Beats Pill but comes at the price of a belt-clip speaker like the JBL Go 3. If you do have a problem, Ortizan's customer service is highly responsive.</p></li> \n</ul> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-smart-speaker-deals">Best Prime Day smart speaker deals</h2> \n<p>Smart speakers aren't just about getting a disembodied voice to do your bidding (or at least as much of your bidding as Alexa can do without hands). On top of assistant support, the picks below serve up legitimately great audio quality alongside useful extra features. The only downside is that they're often overpriced, but that's what Prime Day is for.</p> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09B8V1LZ3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Amazon+Echo+Dot+for+%2432+%2836+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwOUI4VjFMWjM_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjRlY2RkNWItZmYwNi00NDgxLWE0MzktZmRlN2IxNzRjMmM0Iiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwOUI4VjFMWjMiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAf9_JN3Qc98Mx6RGHDd-vPKEhIXbUO8xUB2M0ZQojLmy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09B8V1LZ3"><strong>Amazon Echo Dot for $32 (36 percent off):</strong></a> Amazon may not have updated the Echo Dot since 2022, but that just goes to show how well this spherical smart speaker serves as the perfect host for Alexa. Both music and speech sound clear, and it's easy to integrate with other smart home devices. Right now, it's marked down more than a third.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09WNK39JN&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Amazon+Echo+Pop+for+%2422+%2845+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwOVdOSzM5Sk4_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjRlY2RkNWItZmYwNi00NDgxLWE0MzktZmRlN2IxNzRjMmM0Iiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwOVdOSzM5Sk4iLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZwFoQ3v5qMr6L0HI4OmEke89sDH-b92e3bwz5i3bnxV&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09WNK39JN"><strong>Amazon Echo Pop for $22 (45 percent off):</strong></a> The latest Echo Pop release continues the trend of making Alexa's best features available on a mini-sized, reasonably priced device. Its half-spherical design fits on any desk or shelf, and its sound output is consistently clear — and gets louder than you might believe.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BW34LCB8&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sonos+Era+100+for+%24179+%2810+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATKFMVJbeHTAtkfy4wE8hj70v6mg8-Zw-d2GZSNpt3lB&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSonos-Era-100-Wireless-Speaker%2Fdp%2FB0BW34LCB8%2F"><strong>Sonos Era 100 for $179 (10 percent off):</strong></a> Smart speakers from the Amazon Echo line play perfectly good music, but true audiophiles in need of assistant support should look to Sonos. The Era 100 has tweeters and woofers precisely arranged for clear, full-room sound, and it's easy to hook up to your other audio gear. Just be warned it only supports Alexa, not Google Assistant.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CCK25S7Z&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=JBL+Authentics+200+for+%24200+%2847+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARPrz9HVgvdtZhstuBVOiIvwY-nTRbkhGK7O3251AAEK&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CCK25S7Z"><strong>JBL Authentics 200 for $200 (47 percent off):</strong></a> JBL's Authentics line is modeled after a product it sold in the 70s. Its old-school bookshelf-friendly design belies its advanced feat of running Google Assistant and Alexa simultaneously (as opposed to other smart speakers where you have to pick just one).</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CCK2TFQB&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=JBL+Authentics+300+for+%24285+%2837+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWMK6FNqt3gfLZQucPNvjo-xxoAu0FAlPdTzlh1g86gf&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CCK2TFQB"><strong>JBL Authentics 300 for $285 (37 percent off):</strong></a> The JBL Authentics 300 can host both Alexa and Google Assistant at the same time, which impressed us enough that we gave it <a href="https://www.engadget.com/jbl-authentics-300-review-alexa-and-google-assistant-coexisting-190036434.html">a full review</a>. While we had some issues — namely its tendency to over-emphasize vocals — we can't quibble with its high-range performance or retro design.</p></li> \n</ul> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-soundbar-deals">Best Prime Day soundbar deals</h2> \n<p>Flatter, lighter and larger TV screens are nice for visuals, but often sacrifice sound quality to lose weight. If you've found yourself turning on the subtitles for your shows more often lately, you might need a soundbar to augment your TV's built-in speakers. We found a few of the best on sale for Prime Day — Sonos leads this space, but it's not without competitors.</p> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D6W8XQ6J&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Bose+Smart+for+%24400+%2820+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdfcJUjJgp1-8Bm25hXqVm2C9BMA1DRbdTFPGmzYkOLN&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D6W8XQ6J"><strong>Bose Smart for $400 (20 percent off):</strong></a> In our <a href="https://www.engadget.com/audio/speakers/bose-smart-soundbar-review-using-earbuds-as-surround-sound-speakers-153028639.html">full review</a> of the Bose Smart, we noted that two drivers in the center make its sound feel directional without any other speakers needed — simply cranking up those makes any audio more immersive. You can also link it to a pair of Ultra Open Earbuds (not included) for a private surround sound experience.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0C548MYF3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Bose+Smart+Ultra+for+%24700+%2822+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcXvA4h4-a-DF-S8QCC1dfoW1csVPZbH72w_qouHxc9m&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0C548MYF3"><strong>Bose Smart Ultra for $700 (22 percent off):</strong></a> The Smart Ultra upgrades the Bose Smart with a more sophisticated calibration system which adjusts sound settings to fill whatever room it's in. If you want the Smart's personal surround experience for more than one person, the Smart Ultra is for you.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09GPYL7BJ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sonos+Beam+for+%24369+%2826+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdyuRXzF_Z1UFlPw-STyMD9i_2WvxTWxrBp97AkPSXmV&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09GPYL7BJ"><strong>Sonos Beam for $369 (26 percent off):</strong></a> The Sonos Beam is a fantastic choice for a mid-budget soundbar. It's one of the most accessible Dolby Atmos systems, and uses careful audio alterations to achieve a much more immersive sound than other bars of its size.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0B2KQFTG9&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sonos+Ray+for+%24169+%2815+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAd6bU3WaKjEqWwRNEJIukaEJprnHU68gPZM_LxJ4Gr4V&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0B2KQFTG9"><strong>Sonos Ray for $169 (15 percent off):</strong></a> If you're looking to pay a bit less, go with the Sonos Ray to maximize sound quality on a budget. The audio won't wrap around your room like it might from a more premium model, but it's still a vast improvement on nearly all built-in TV speakers.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CXZTT4MT&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Amazon+Fire+TV+Plus+for+%24150+%2840+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARpHpjRH4DyA5SlaP3sTudgYmfzVwzH__oaLPHRb6f8y&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FIntroducing-Amazon-Soundbar-channel-design%2Fdp%2FB0CXZTT4MT%2F"><strong>Amazon Fire TV Plus for $150 (40 percent off):</strong></a> Amazon's latest Fire TV soundbar is built for streaming TV and emphasizing dialogue. If you have any other Amazon TVs or streaming devices, you'll find it easy to integrate with your existing hardware — you can even use the same remote to control them all.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09SQWQ4TC&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sony+HT-S400+for+%24178+%2841+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcWKT2m0IQG2xX9Aswzd4Y9LDMRRkCRepSBwD1-LQiCk&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09SQWQ4TC"><strong>Sony HT-S400 for $178 (41 percent off):</strong></a> Sony <a href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-ht-s400-soundbar-171654014.html">built the HT-S400</a> for everyone who wants a soundbar but not an entire home theater. It's a 2.1-channel system that still manages immersive surround sound and is easy to integrate with Sony TVs. Right now, it's 40 percent off, one of the best prices we've seen on any soundbar.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DYWPJYF1&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sony+Bravia+Theater+Bar+6+for+%24448+%2831+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARfMGfExzqY8QimFqx6HwJQG-JdM-GiOzvHokFZCSb2P&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-Powerful-Wireless-subwoofer-Surround%2Fdp%2FB0DYWPJYF1%2F"><strong>Sony Bravia Theater Bar 6 for $448 (31 percent off):</strong></a> One of Sony's <a href="https://www.engadget.com/home/home-theater/sony-adds-the-bravia-theater-bar-6-to-its-dolby-atmos-soundbar-lineup-160012544.html">newest audio products</a>, the Bravia Theater Bar 6 is a 3.1.2 soundbar that can bend audio in more directions to fill your theater space. It can handle Dolby Atmos, and has an integrated AI feature that recognizes and clarifies human voices.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CVCMCL2K&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=VIZIO+2.0+for+%2478+%2822+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYav37udvI709Zg5zopPiZr0C6XXCdrTollWvvOZFTw0&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CVCMCL2K"><strong>VIZIO 2.0 for $78 (22 percent off):</strong></a> Vizio's budget soundbar makes a worthy alternative to the Sonos Ray. It punches above its weight and gets as close as possible to Dolby Atmos surround sound as a single unit can manage. For less than $100, you'll never mishear a line of dialogue again.</p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B084KGSV4Q&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=24ecdd5b-ff06-4481-a439-fde7b174c2c4&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=JBL+Bar+9.1+for+%24760+%2837+percent+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVdLVzDBjlmJSooLWltI-jkWw_73eZ5n6Fv3LW7qwb9h&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB084KGSV4Q"><strong>JBL Bar 9.1 for $760 (37 percent off):</strong></a> The 9.1 is JBL's first sound bar to be compatible with Dolby Atmos, and it doesn't disappoint. Each unit comes with two wireless speakers you can move around your viewing room, and there's even a 4K passthrough input to ensure your sound system doesn't mess with image quality.</p></li> \n</ul>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-best-prime-day-speaker-deals-last-chance-to-get-up-to-47-percent-off-on-jbl-bose-sonos-and-others-085948445.html?src=rss	2025-07-12 00:15:35	Sam Chapman	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.481547
375	14	Best Prime Day deals on Amazon devices: It's the last day to get up to 68 percent off Kindle ereaders, Echo speakers and more	https://www.engadget.com/deals/best-prime-day-deals-on-amazon-devices-its-the-last-day-to-get-up-to-68-percent-off-kindle-ereaders-echo-speakers-and-more-082012880.html?src=rss	<p>If you’re on the market for a Kindle, Fire TV device or Echo speaker, <a href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-prime-day/">Amazon Prime Day</a> is basically Black Friday for you. Prime Day deals on those devices are typically the same (or very close to) the prices we see at the end of the year near the holidays. That means now is a great time to pick up a new Kindle ereader ahead of the new semester in the fall, a Fire TV Stick for streaming while traveling or an Echo speaker for your home office. As expected, almost all of Amazon’s hardware is on sale for Prime Day; these are the best Prime Day deals on Amazon gear that are still available on the last day of the sale.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-prime-day-echo-deals">Prime Day Echo deals</h2> \n<p>\n </p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09ZXJDSL5&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=3701263a-2e01-47ef-8a44-7c0103d90a18&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Echo+Pop+speaker+for+%2422+%2845+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwOVpYSkRTTDU_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMzcwMTI2M2EtMmUwMS00N2VmLThhNDQtN2MwMTAzZDkwYTE4Iiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwOVpYSkRTTDUiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAeNLKqfvQ32Yl9jDgoOexhsfpVEW2oSl4YYBJa-EcoT4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09ZXJDSL5"><strong>Echo Pop speaker for $22 (45 percent off):</strong></a> One of the newer Echo devices available, the Pop it sports a 1.95-inch front-facing speaker and a physical mic mute switch for extra privacy. The Pop also has built-in eero compatibility, so it can extend the area of your home Wi-Fi network if you already have an eero router system.</p> <span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>\n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09B2SBHQK&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=3701263a-2e01-47ef-8a44-7c0103d90a18&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Echo+Show+5+for+%2460+%2833+percent+off%29%3A&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwOUIyU0JIUUs_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMzcwMTI2M2EtMmUwMS00N2VmLThhNDQtN2MwMTAzZDkwYTE4Iiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwOUIyU0JIUUsiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAXNc4qYBjoQ3BSw8d9PohOkZOIP3R_NAJCxrTG9r-QiM&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09B2SBHQK"><strong>Echo Show 5 for $60 (33 percent off):</strong></a> This model is one of our favorite <a href="https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-display-202448797.html">smart displays</a> thanks to its compact design, ambient light sensor and sunrise alarm feature, all of which make it an excellent smart alarm clock. Amazon improved the speaker quality on this latest model, which gives sound deeper bass and clearer vocals.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BLS3Y632&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=3701263a-2e01-47ef-8a44-7c0103d90a18&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchant