id" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BPMTJJ6D&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Final+Fantasy+XVI&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQlBNVEpKNkQ_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjkzMzVhM2QtZTMwYS00NjJhLWJjOTgtZWQwMzdhNTA1MDA2Iiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQlBNVEpKNkQiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdVlMNrGxZVBCJsPmq6LhE_EXE94qVIBQ4y8HVH_PIgL&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BPMTJJ6D"><em>Final Fantasy XVI</em></a> ($25, $15 off)</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-deals-on-vr-headsets">Best Prime Day deals on VR headsets</h2> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0F2GYMC8H&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Meta+Quest+3S+128GB+Bundle+for+%24249+%28%2451+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAepE5rK0kewyeLBzsqqXh9JJ5B8M3uFW98PkYPBhQVVg&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMeta-Quest-128GB-Cardboard-Exclusive-Oculus%2Fdp%2FB0F2GYMC8H">Meta Quest 3S 128GB Bundle for $249 ($51 off)</a></p> \n<p>The Quest 3S is one of our picks for <a href="https://www.engadget.com/ar-vr/best-vr-headsets-140012529.html">best VR headsets</a> for good reason. Meta cut just the right corners from the more full-featured Quest 3, enabling it to drop the list price down lower. It has the same Snapdragon chip and controlers, but cheaps out a bit on the lenses, slightly lowering the graphics fidelity in use. Just like the Quest 3, it works standalone for lighter games and streaming, or in concert with a gaming PC for full-fat AAA VR titles. It's well worth the $300 Meta usually asks for it, so at $249 with two games included (<em>Cardboard Hero</em> and the excellent social VR hit <em>Gorilla Tag</em>), it's a steal.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-deals-on-pcs-and-pc-components"><strong>Best Prime Day deals on </strong>PCs and PC components</h2> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=d043077a-4ba1-4321-a933-30b8701d8d31&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Razer&amp;linkText=Razer+Blade+14+with+RTX+4070+for+%242%2C300+%28%24400+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfSK1oR7YwimfMZ-Ox-UX8iBbldRpVlvDjEYxuEAw0nM&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.razer.com%2Fgaming-laptops%2FRazer-Blade-14%2FRZ09-05306ES3-R3U1">Razer Blade 14 with RTX 4070 for $2,300 ($400 off)</a></p> \n<p>The Blade 14 is one of my favorite laptop lines because it combines a super sleek chassis with solid performance and truly excellent build quality. And now, as a way to get in on the Prime Day festivities, Razer has an exclusive offer on its website that will knock $400 off configs with RTX 4070 GPUs or up to <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=d043077a-4ba1-4321-a933-30b8701d8d31&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Razer&amp;linkText=%24300+on+models+with+RTX+4060+cards&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAV-FqEzsJtTRhJ4vTvWt1Hh7Baeh6RGyXl5tLel7CTzf&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.razer.com%2Fgaming-laptops%2Frazer-blade-14%2FRZ09-05305ES3-R3U1">$300 on models with RTX 4060 cards</a>. These kind of savings go a long way towards neutralizing my biggest issue with Razer's laptops: their price. So if you're looking for a system that can do some serious gaming but is still easy to carry around, you're going to want to snap this deal up fast.&nbsp;</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DVZSG8D5&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=AMD+Ryzen+9+9950X3D+16-Core+processor+for+%24664+%28%2435+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRFZaU0c4RDU_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjkzMzVhM2QtZTMwYS00NjJhLWJjOTgtZWQwMzdhNTA1MDA2Iiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRFZaU0c4RDUiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdZcWlXI0aab7NpzTI7WyvFcHAuQYswcbtd0UkawCdSu&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0DVZSG8D5">AMD Ryzen 9 9950X3D 16-Core processor for $664 ($35 off)</a></p> \n<p>AMD's X3D chips are the cream of the crop when it comes to gaming performance and while it's only enjoying a $35 discount right now, informed buyers know that the real savings are bigger than that because these chips often go for well above their MSRP. But the best thing is that for Prime Day, in addition to the 9950X3D, there are a bunch of other X3D processors on sale right now including the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DKFMSMYK&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=%24460+Ryzen+7+9800X3D&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdm9PGzt5FfMhLW_uJefcE-F6yNXjAiJg9TlP42w5Siu&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAMD-9800X3D-16-Thread-Desktop-Processor%2Fdp%2FB0DKFMSMYK%2F">$460 Ryzen 7 9800X3D</a> and <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CQ4H4H7X&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=%24265+Ryzen+7+5700X3D&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZ7B6xsRqv_TrpRj56wkuKTvHnQ4rFpzIbfjafR_wBD3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAMD-Ryzen-5700X3D-16-Thread-Processor%2Fdp%2FB0CQ4H4H7X">$265 Ryzen 7 5700X3D</a> so you can pick the right component for your budget. If you need a new CPU to speed up your gaming rig, now is a great time to upgrade.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CRCYJ8YV&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=ASUS+ROG+Strix+G16+Gaming+Laptop+with+RTX+4060+for+%241%2C360+%28%24340+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdOdcTvc3l_lMGyLJevaAy49UZY409t5OSpe4MwS8PWs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FASUS-Gaming-Laptop-Nebula-Display%2Fdp%2FB0CRCYJ8YV%2F">ASUS ROG Strix G16 Gaming Laptop with RTX 4060 for $1,360 ($340 off)</a></p> \n<p>While an RTX 4060 isn't the most powerful GPU on the market, getting a whole new laptop with solid specs for just $1,360 isn't something you can just ignore, especially if you're on a budget. This ROG Strix G16 comes with 16GB of RAM and 1TB of storage. And while its Intel Core i9-14900HX CPU is one generation old, it's still plenty fast enough for gaming, video editing or pretty much anything else you need to do. I also appreciate small features like a MUX switch that lets the laptop connect directly to the GPU for increased performance, though if you want, you can also enable automatic switching for better battery life. And with a 16-inch 240Hz QHD display with 100% DCI-P3 coverage, everything on screen is sure to look great.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D8JZDJBG&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Acer+Nitro+V+gaming+laptop+with+NVIDIA+RTX+4060+GPU+for+%241%2C200+%28%24150+off%2C+lowest+ever+price%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2k5LTEzOTAwSC1Qcm9jZXNzb3ItR2VGb3JjZS1EaXNwbGF5LUFOVjE1LTUxLTkyWEsvZHAvQjBEOEpaREpCRy8_&amp;signature=AQAAAROYeEqMSrBpVsEW7crAkhhgEGqpmnQfA7JRHryo0EC4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fi9-13900H-Processor-GeForce-Display-ANV15-51-92XK%2Fdp%2FB0D8JZDJBG%2F">Acer Nitro V gaming laptop with NVIDIA RTX 4060 GPU for $1,200 ($150 off, lowest ever price)</a></p> \n<p>Acer's Nitro gaming laptops are meant to be more affordable alternatives to its flagship Predator systems. But now thanks to Prime Day, this model just got even more budget-friendly while still offering decent specs. You get an Intel Core i9-13900H CPU with 32GB of RAM, 1TB of storage and an RTX 4060 GPU, the latter of which should pair nicely with its 15.6-inch full HD 144Hz display. I also appreciate that unlike some gaming laptops, the Nitro V is stylish without being in your face with too many RGB lights, which makes it feel like an even better deal at $1,200. That's the lowest price we've seen to date for this configuration.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BZHTVHN5&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Corsair+Vengeance+RGB+DDR5+RAM+32GB+%282x16GB%29+RAM+for+%2495+%28%2425+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZ20xSg-pl-iG3x7gi3-FPu3nUVPxhNAVJkkAJGy9cGU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCORSAIR-VENGEANCE-6000MHz-Compatible-Computer%2Fdp%2FB0BZHTVHN5">Corsair Vengeance RGB DDR5 RAM 32GB (2x16GB) RAM for $95 ($25 off)</a></p> \n<p>Adding some extra memory to your desktop can help unlock its full potential. So for Prime Day, Corsair is offering two 16GB sticks of its Vengeance DDR5 RAM for just $95. Not only do you get built-in RGB lighting, Corsair's onboard voltage regulation makes it simpler to overclock your system. And for those who don't want to mess around in BIOS settings, you can control almost everything from the easy-to-use free iCue app.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CKY88GMT&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Thermaltake+GF1+%282024%29+Fully+Modular+ATX+850W+Power+Supply+for+%2480+%28%2430+off%2C+lowest+ever+price%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1RoZXJtYWx0YWtlLUZ1bGx5LU1vZHVsYXItUG93ZXItU3VwcGx5L2RwL0IwQ0tZODhHTVQ_&amp;signature=AQAAAab1tzjHVvLcMBmk8E261YBZTJF89Lgb09yFSGUvz44T&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FThermaltake-Fully-Modular-Power-Supply%2Fdp%2FB0CKY88GMT">Thermaltake GF1 (2024) Fully Modular ATX 850W Power Supply for $80 ($30 off, lowest ever price)</a></p> \n<p>Even though power supplies aren't the most exciting component you can put in your desktop, the importance of a good one can't be understated. For just $80, which is the lowest price we've seen to date for this product, the Thermaltake GF1 is fully modular (which means you can add or remove power cables as you need them) and has an ample max power of 850 watts along with an 80 Plus Gold rating for efficiency. And thanks to its 140mm fan, it should be pretty quiet, so it won't cause a ruckus if you decide to play some games at night.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DHLCRF91&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+990+EVO+Plus+2TB+PCIe+M.2+SSD+for+%24114+%28%2463+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NBTVNVTkctVGVjaG5vbG9neS1JbnRlbGxpZ2VudC1UdXJib3dyaXRlLU1aLVY5UzJUMEIvZHAvQjBESExDUkY5MS8_&amp;signature=AQAAAXzZz7oy5iP6Nw7XA_JcvSMDfGFq5ALQTISVP3UjiHXP&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Technology-Intelligent-Turbowrite-MZ-V9S2T0B%2Fdp%2FB0DHLCRF91%2F">Samsung 990 EVO Plus 2TB PCIe M.2 SSD for $114 ($63 off)</a></p> \n<p>If you're like me and are constantly running out of storage, this deal for one of Samsung's 990 EVO Plus 2TB M.2 SSDs is a fantastic way to add extra room on the cheap. With a 36 percent discount for Prime Day — down to $114 — this is the lowest price we've ever seen. And it's not like you're cutting corners on speed either, as the SSD supports both PCIe 4.0 x4 and PCIe 5.0 x2 and read/write rates of up to 7,250/6,300MB/s.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D6NN6TM7&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=AMD+Ryzen+5+9600X+6-Core%2C+12-Thread+Unlocked+Processor+for+%24156+%28%24123+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0FNRC1SeXplblRNLTk2MDBYLTEyLVRocmVhZC1Qcm9jZXNzb3IvZHAvQjBENk5ONlRNNy8_&amp;signature=AQAAAdxfDcQcUjruAY-rfAqHWDpyGTPpSa7pOLp-GeqZI97e&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAMD-RyzenTM-9600X-12-Thread-Processor%2Fdp%2FB0D6NN6TM7%2F">AMD Ryzen 5 9600X 6-Core, 12-Thread Unlocked Processor for $156 ($123 off)</a></p> \n<p>The Ryzen 5 9600X isn't super flashy, but it's a really solid budget CPU. And now, it’s even more affordable during Prime Day where it's going for just $156, which is $123 off its normal retail price. It features six cores and 12 total threads with a max boost speed of 5.4GHz and support for DDR5 RAM and PCIe Gen 5. It's also unlocked, so you have the freedom to overlock if you want. That said, you will need to buy a CPU cooler separately, as one doesn't come in the box.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D6NNRBGP&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=AMD+Ryzen+9+9950X+16-Core%2C+32-Thread+Unlocked+Desktop+Processor+for+%24434+%28%24215+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0FNRC1SeXplblRNLTk5NTBYLTMyLVRocmVhZC1Qcm9jZXNzb3IvZHAvQjBENk5OUkJHUC8_&amp;signature=AQAAAclhL5oTFTmv7bWwarssGvVsinY-EojaV22pOQbJ_RCO&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAMD-RyzenTM-9950X-32-Thread-Processor%2Fdp%2FB0D6NNRBGP%2F">AMD Ryzen 9 9950X 16-Core, 32-Thread Unlocked Desktop Processor for $434 ($215 off)</a></p> \n<p>The biggest issue with the Ryzen 9 9950X CPU was that at launch, it was a bit overpriced. But during Prime Day, that problem is being addressed thanks to a $215 discount that brings its cost down to under $500. The CPU features 16 cores and 32 threads along with 80MB of cache and support for DDR5 RAM and PCIe Gen 5. However, like some of AMD's other processors on sale this week, you will need to get a CPU cooler separately.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-deals-on-gaming-peripherals"><strong>Best Prime Day deals on gaming p</strong>eripherals</h2> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CGGT138N&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Razer+Enki+Gaming+Chair+for+%24450+%28%2450+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1JhemVyLUVua2ktR2FtaW5nLUNoYWlyLUJ1aWx0L2RwL0IwQ0dHVDEzOE4_&amp;signature=AQAAAYvX30CfwZWhHIFFgxs2H8veYfvjTyKgoCg1fUYiLQDE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Enki-Gaming-Chair-Built%2Fdp%2FB0CGGT138N">Razer Enki Gaming Chair for $450 ($50 off)</a></p> \n<p>If you're going to be spending all day in front of a screen gaming, you better make sure whatever you're sitting on is super comfy. And as I've been using the Razer Enki every day for the last four years, I can attest that this chair is worth the money. It has a ton of adjustability for things like the arm rests, seat height and more. For more flexible folks, it was even designed so people can sit cross-legged. I also appreciate that in homes where neon green might not fit your vibe, there's an all-black model (plus a pink one too, though that one is currently sold out).</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09ZWCYQTX&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=SteelSeries+Arctis+Nova+Pro+wireless+headset+for+%24323+%28%2450+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATi5JRF6ZsgGvqQyRdofnHsz_ZSFPj6o7tQtTPXr15-z&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSteelSeries-Arctis-Wireless-Multi-System-Headset%2Fdp%2FB09ZWCYQTX%2F">SteelSeries Arctis Nova Pro wireless headset for $323 ($50 off)</a></p> \n<p>SteelSeries makes some of the most comfortable headsets I've ever used thanks to the super soft earcups equipped on every pair. But what separates the Arctis Nova Pro from lesser competitors is support for premium features like 360-degree spatial audio, strong noise cancellation and a hot swap battery system. Butthe best feature is SteelSeries' dedicated base station, which features an OLED screen, physical knobs and dual USB ports so you can connect your headset to multiple devices and swap between audio sources with the touch of a button.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09738CV2G&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Elgato+Stream+Deck+MK.2+for+%24110+%28%2440+off%2C+lowest+ever%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0VsZ2F0by1TdHJlYW0tRGVjay1NSy0yLUNvbnRyb2xsZXIvZHAvQjA5NzM4Q1YyRy8_&amp;signature=AQAAAXAZ7Lkb497mhUihCk94SkCXLHrkvnKCg7yzfm9lrWkO&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FElgato-Stream-Deck-MK-2-Controller%2Fdp%2FB09738CV2G%2F">Elgato Stream Deck MK.2 for $110 ($40 off, lowest ever)</a></p> \n<p>If you've ever dreamed about becoming a gaming streamer or simply want some extra customizable controls for your PC, Elgato's Stream Deck MK.2 could make a great addition to your setup. It has 15 programmable macro keys with built-in LCD displays so you can make custom buttons for switching scenes, turning on lights and so much more. Elgato also has plugins for services like YouTube, Twitch, Discord, so it'll play nicely with all the major streaming platforms. In short, it's like a command center for all your content creation and livestreaming needs.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B07CMS5Q6P&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Logitech+G305+Lightspeed+Wireless+Gaming+Mouse+for+%2429+%28%2421+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0xvZ2l0ZWNoLUxJR0hUU1BFRUQtV2lyZWxlc3MtR2FtaW5nLU1vdXNlL2RwL0IwN0NNUzVRNlA_&amp;signature=AQAAAesqBBN6TW1sKTRSr67E_VXqmZLe-rlIPM_ipSNj4ssS&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLogitech-LIGHTSPEED-Wireless-Gaming-Mouse%2Fdp%2FB07CMS5Q6P">Logitech G305 Lightspeed Wireless Gaming Mouse for $29 ($21 off)</a></p> \n<p>The Logitech G305 Lightspeed gaming mouse is just a simple PC peripheral done well. And at just $29, it's super affordable during Prime Day too. It features six programmable buttons, compatibility with both PCs and Macs and a sensor with sensitivity of up to 12,000 DPI. Meanwhile, thanks to a battery that lasts up to 250 hours between charges, you can go weeks between needing to plug it in. And because it's wireless, there won't be any cords or cables to get in your way.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0B2BZWGRK&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Amazon+Luna+Controller+and+one+month+of+Luna%2B+for+%2440+%28%2430+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAR-ib1Bs4T5df_U-kjstGjwFRX9iuL7Pq2ZYoKKbdOeh&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0B2BZWGRK%2F">Amazon Luna Controller and one month of Luna+ for $40 ($30 off)</a></p> \n<p>The Luna Controller by itself is <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B07P989QTJ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=down+to+%2440&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZOGIwDAqMZlPuRNxBOJZfSmC_Bw-cRuxAY-p9DEdeJh&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07P989QTJ%2F">down to $40</a>, which matches a record-low price. However, if you're a newcomer to Luna+, you may as well pick up this bundle (which is also matching a record low) for the same price, as it includes one month of access to the service for new subscribers. This gamepad is a solid option for those who want to check out Luna, Amazon's cloud gaming service. Prime subscribers get access to a dedicated channel with a rotating selection of games at no extra cost. This month, for instance, you can check out <em>Death Stranding Director's Cut, Hollow Knight</em> and <em>EA Sports FC 25</em>.&nbsp;</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D4QB5HMZ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=8BitDo+Retro+Mechanical+Keyboard+for+%2480+%28%2420+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdmY9UjJ9zZOUk0AQh9j_6rsXVUqufk0jfzLHqg0gb7-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMechanical-Bluetooth-Swappable-Gaming-Programmable-Console%2Fdp%2FB0D4QB5HMZ">8BitDo Retro Mechanical Keyboard for $80 ($20 off)</a></p> \n<p>With its Retro Mechanical Keyboard, 8BitDo strikes a great balance between a nostalgic design and support for more modern features like wireless connectivity (both BT and 2.4GHz). There are several different versions to choose from, though the one inspired by the classic NES is the model I'd choose. The keyboard features an 87-key layout with PBT keycaps and Kailh Box switches, though because the PCB is hot swappable, you can always change them out for something else.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CJH3DJ36&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sony+Inzone+H9+Wireless+Gaming+Headset+for+%24198+%28%24102+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYStzjRN0t_IMHQfAmX7s_j2sotDS3DD3nWlLp8Bn0kY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-Wireless-Canceling-Over-Ear-Headphones%2Fdp%2FB0CJH3DJ36">Sony Inzone H9 Wireless Gaming Headset for $198 ($102 off)</a></p> \n<p>For anyone looking for a new pair of over-the-ear wireless gaming headphones to pair with a PS5, it's hard to do better than <a href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-inzone-gaming-hardware-hands-on-specs-price-availability-210013674.html">Sony's Inzone H9 headset.</a> Not only does it have a similar design to the console, they are the only other headphones besides the official Pulse cans that support on-screen status notifications for volume, mic mute, game/chat balance and more. They also share a lot of the underlying tech used in Sony's iconic WH-1000XM line, so you'll get fantastic audio quality and active noise cancellation. But the best part is that at $198, you're looking at a serious discount of 34 percent, which is more than $100 off its regular retail price.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09BJYXMDW&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Seagate+Storage+Expansion+Card+2TB+Solid+State+Drive+for+%24209+%28%2421+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NlYWdhdGUtU3RvcmFnZS1FeHBhbnNpb24tU29saWQtU3RhdGUvZHAvQjA5QkpZWE1EVy8_&amp;signature=AQAAAa4MphOzGbLvN2-ceLFLcu7lHu2Gny6G2pMIRr4S-R3b&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSeagate-Storage-Expansion-Solid-State%2Fdp%2FB09BJYXMDW%2F">Seagate Storage Expansion Card 2TB Solid State Drive for $209 ($21 off)</a></p> \n<p>Games are getting bigger every day, so if you need some extra storage for your Xbox Series S or X, you'd be silly not to pick up one of Seagate's 2TB Expansion Cards for just $209. That's enough room for a dozen or more digital titles (or like three versions of <em>Call of Duty) </em>and it's the biggest SSD storage module that slots into the back of the console without the need for a separate box.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B073Q3BSPG&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Amazon+Basics+UPS+Battery+Backup+%26+Surge+Protector+800VA%2F450W+for+%2465+%28%2410+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARMEKKVzhKw_9ZaGLLoLVnPjY0v9PXIjDv1hf6x-teD9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAmazonBasics-Standby-UPS-800VA-Outlets%2Fdp%2FB073Q3BSPG%2F">Amazon Basics UPS Battery Backup &amp; Surge Protector 800VA/450W for $65 ($10 off)</a></p> \n<p>I'm not here to nag, but if you have a desktop PC, you really ought to consider adding a UPS (uninterruptible power supply) to your setup as they prevent power surges or momentary outages from knocking your system offline. Plus, this one has a beefy 450-watt battery backup and 12 outlets so you can connect all of your other PC gadgets to it. So if you're going to do the smart thing by adding some extra electrical protection to your home during Prime Day, you might as well save some money in the process.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-deals-on-mobile-gaming-gear"><strong>Best Prime Day deals on </strong>mobile gaming gear</h2> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DP3G4GVQ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+Galaxy+S25+Ultra+%28512GB%29+for+%241%2C055+%28%24365+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAe98iEihI7z-FCHF2NPx7mzOKzfKglqqgrzgzntCatn0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSmartphone-Unlocked-Processor-Manufacturer-Warranty%2Fdp%2FB0DP3G4GVQ%2F">Samsung Galaxy S25 Ultra (512GB) for $1,055 ($365 off)</a></p> \n<p>With <a href="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/what-to-expect-at-the-next-samsung-galaxy-unpacked-150001731.html">Samsung's next Unpacked event</a> expected to show off new foldables, it looks like some of the existing models are getting some serious discounts for Prime Day, including the Galaxy S25 Ultra. And at $1,055, this is the lowest price we've seen for Samsung's current flagship phone yet. For gamers, thanks to its Snapdragon 8 Elite chip, the S25 Ultra offers some of the best performance you can get in a phone right now, while its built-in vapor chamber should help prevent throttling. Its 6.9-inch AMOLED display is also one of the best mobile screens on the market today.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CXGMPLWK&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Razer+Kishi+Ultra+for+%24100+%28%2450+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbVWeNQyF5LXHKm9GsLVr2Uw4TS4uCeeJYSj0esaqI87&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Gaming-Controller-Android-iPhone-Smartphone%2Fdp%2FB0CXGMPLWK">Razer Kishi Ultra for $100 ($50 off)</a></p> \n<p>Razer doesn't normally run a ton of deals for Prime Day, but it seems this year the company is making an exception as there are discounts on <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=everything+from+gamepads+to+headsets+and+more&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUgljZ3Kp6d2QUOrtZW87gdjjzLfwYidwJ5ra6JxYXd-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fstores%2Fpage%2F03508F9D-3610-49AC-9E57-C476A4E7B219">everything from gamepads to headsets and more</a>. That said, one of the standout deals is for the <a href="https://www.engadget.com/razers-kishi-ultra-gaming-controller-works-with-damn-near-everything-including-some-foldables-173017166.html">Kishi Ultra gaming controller</a>. On top of just being a well-built gamepad add-on for phones and tablets, its larger dimension and USB-C port means it works with a huge range of devices — both Android and iOS. This even includes more niche devices like foldables like the Galaxy Z Fold series, which often don't fit inside other mobile gamepads due to their unique design.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CCT2LWT8&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Backbone+One+mobile+controller+for+Android+and+iPhone+15%2F16+for+%2470+%28%2430+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARabIAL67BSMNtwkfu5Eov6CQcoVtjhKfCuNHbc-9tsT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBACKBONE-Mobile-Gaming-Controller-Android-iOS%2Fdp%2FB0CCT2LWT8%2F">Backbone One mobile controller for Android and iPhone 15/16 for $70 ($30 off)</a></p> \n<p>If you like playing games on your phone but prefer real joysticks and buttons, the Backbone One is a great accessory. It's compatible with a ton of big-name titles like Call of Duty, the Xbox Game Pass and GeForce Now. Though sadly because this isn't the PlayStation Edition, Android users can’t use this with the PS Remote Play app. Regardless, you still get solid physical controls along with a 3.5mm jack for pass-through audio. But the most important thing is that because this model features USB-C, it works with pretty much any recent Android phone and late-model Apple handsets like the iPhone 15 and 16.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-deals-on-gaming-monitors-and-tvs"><strong>Best Prime Day deals on gaming m</strong>onitors and TVs</h2> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CVPCLY6X&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Sony+85-Inch+Class+4K+Ultra+HD+Bravia+3+LED+TV+for+%241%2C098+%28%24500+off%29&amp;_cz1lbGVjdHJvbmljcyIsImR5bmFtaWNDZW50cmFsVHJhY2tpbmdJZCI6dHJ1ZSwic2l0ZUlkIjoidXMtZW5nYWRnZXQiLCJwYWdlSWQiOiIxcC1hdXRvbGluayIsImZlYXR1cmVJZCI6InRleHQtbGluayJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZG7stZXKNLk52nDF2u1L8gmG71GbFXI8Nc3X1FwnAbN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSony-85-Inch-Exclusive-Features-PlayStation%2525C2%2525AE5%2Fdp%2FB0CVPCLY6X%2Fref%3Dsr_1_1%3Fs%3Delectronics">Sony 85-Inch Class 4K Ultra HD Bravia 3 LED TV for $1,098 ($500 off)</a></p> \n<p>There's no better way to upgrade your living room gaming setup than with a brand-new, big-ass TV. Granted, the Bravia 3 is one of Sony's entry-level models (fancier sets get higher numbers), but with a discounted price of $1,098 for a massive 85-inch panel, this deal represents one of the biggest screens you can get for the money. It also has Google TV built in, so you'll get a very simple and straightforward way to stream your favorite shows and movies from services like Netflix, HBO and more. But perhaps most importantly is that for PS5 owners, the Bravia 3 supports exclusive features when connected to a PS5, such as Auto HDR Tone Mapping and Auto Genre Picture mode.</p> \n<p>By the way, for a more in-depth look at the best TV discounts, check out our dedicated guide covering <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/amazon-prime-day-tv-deals-for-2025-from-sony-lg-samsung-and-others-084705639.html"><strong>the best TV deals for Amazon Prime Day 2025</strong></a><strong>.</strong></p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=5e0bed65-d2f8-4b34-9b8f-955218c0e37a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Best+Buy&amp;linkText=LG+UltraGear+32-inch+OLED+Dual+Mode+gaming+monitor+for+%241%2C000+%28%24400+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUgYZ01vozabNDf4V4yIyCY1TXtHfZsR-NK9hGtbw-kF&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fsite%2Flg-ultragear-32-oled-dual-mode-4k-uhd-240hzfhd-480hz-0-03ms-nvidia-g-sync-compatible-amd-freesync-pro-gaming-monitor-white%2F6595425.p">LG UltraGear 32-inch OLED Dual Mode gaming monitor for $1,000 ($400 off)</a></p> \n<p>LG's dual mode 32-inch UltraGear monitor is one of the best displays for PC gaming out right now and as part of Prime Day, Best Buy has it on sale for $400 off. You can set it to 4K at 240Hz for when you want a sharp, high-resolution view. Or you can switch it to full HD, which allows its refresh rate to jump all the way up to 480Hz, which is more than enough for even the most demanding competitive gamer. It also supports AMD FreeSync Pro and because it's based on an OLED panel, you get pure blacks and vibrant colors along. The one small downside is that it doesn't have the most impressive peak brightness. But considering everything else this monitor offers, getting one for $1,000 feels like a steal.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CZSGWLD5&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Alienware+AW2725DF+26.7-inch+OLED+gaming+monitor+for+%24600+%28%24300+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0FsaWVud2FyZS1BVzI3MjVERi1PTEVELUdhbWluZy1Nb25pdG9yL2RwL0IwQ1pTR1dMRDU_&amp;signature=AQAAATp7u50btFG6FjunwfkpQLAenqgUFZnYEOZpaCjqcr2t&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAlienware-AW2725DF-OLED-Gaming-Monitor%2Fdp%2FB0CZSGWLD5">Alienware AW2725DF 26.7-inch OLED gaming monitor for $600 ($300 off)</a></p> \n<p>For anyone who has been waiting for prices of OLED gaming monitors to drop, this may be your chance to pounce on a great deal. That's because at $600, Alienware's 26.7-inch OLED display strikes a good balance between price and performance with a 360Hz refresh rate, 2560 x 1440 resolution and support for AMD FreeSync Premium Pro. And of course, you get those lovely pure blacks and vivid colors that OLED panels have become known for.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CDQM55C9&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+Odyssey+Neo+G9+Series+57-inch+4K+240Hz+4K+gaming+monitor+for+%241%2C600+%28%24700+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAU8Mp7X6QBxwUHzWyicpamkuxTTbjU6yXi5rU-YLdpbS&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-DisplayPort-Mini-LED-DisplayHDR-LS57CG952NNXZA%2Fdp%2FB0CDQM55C9">Samsung Odyssey Neo G9 Series 57-inch 4K 240Hz 4K gaming monitor for $1,600 ($700 off)</a></p> \n<p>This 57-inch monitor isn't for people with limited space. But if you've got the room, at $1,600, this is the lowest we've ever seen the Neo G9 as this deal represents a whopping $700 savings compared to its regular list price. This thing features a solid 240Hz refresh rate along with support for AMD FreeSync Premium Pro, a 1000R curve and Quantum mini LED tech with 2,392 local dimming zones. For people who love ultra-wide displays, this should be at the top of your upgrade list during Amazon Prime Day.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0C4Z8RFY9&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Acer+Nitro+27-inch+WQHD+IPS+gaming+monitor+for+%24170+%28%24120+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfb02txFQYbvD2YO7usCrkwG_1wxtJ_6JUVEE_C-chY0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAcer-Monitor-FreeSync-Premium-M3bmiiprx%2Fdp%2FB0C4Z8RFY9">Acer Nitro 27-inch WQHD IPS gaming monitor for $170 ($120 off)</a></p> \n<p>Anyone looking for a solid and affordable 1440p gaming monitor during Prime Day should really check out this 27-inch IPS display from Acer. For just $170 (matching a record-low price), it features a relatively speedy 180Hz refresh rate along with support for AMD FreeSync Premium and a good color range that covers 95 percent of DCI-P3. The height-adjustable stand can also swivel and pivot, while thin bezels on top and on the sides will make sure it won't look dated in a few years. So while this thing isn't super fancy, it's simple and competent in the best ways.</p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-best-prime-day-deals-on-batteries-and-power-packs"><strong>Best Prime Day deals on b</strong>atteries and power packs</h2> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CH33F5P2&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=UGREEN+Magnetic+Power+Bank+10%2C000mAh+fast+charging+battery+pack+for+%2433+%28%242+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAan1J2_CGnG_lLQv3W9rOYl11WQabu33A4pkt8cCuxE5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FUGREEN-10000mAh-Magnetic-Power-Black%2Fdp%2FB0CH33F5P2">UGREEN Magnetic Power Bank 10,000mAh fast charging battery pack for $33 ($2 off)</a></p> \n<p>The Switch 2 is a fantastic handheld, but its longevity could be better. So if you're planning to take it on a long trip, pick up UGREEN's 10,000mAH fast charging battery pack to help keep running when you're away from a plug. This power pack almost has enough juice to fully refill a Switch 2 twice, which can add between five and 12 hours of additional game time (depending on the title). It also has an output of 20 watts, which is as much as the Switch 2 can suck down at once, but it's still super pocketable measuring just four inches long and 0.7 inches thick. And if you need a convenient way to recharge your phone, the battery pack also comes with Qi wireless support.</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B091BFJGLL&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=29335a3d-e30a-462a-bc98-ed037a505006&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=24-pack+Tenergy+Premium+PRO+Rechargeable+AA+and+AAA+batteries+for+%2436+%28%247+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAevZrP7j6H0KhwSCAms8alnXKPGiyac7qcINu25Mcp8l&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FTenergy-Premium-Rechargeable-Batteries-Capacity%2Fdp%2FB091BFJGLL%2F"><ins>24-pack Tenergy Premium PRO Rechargeable AA and AAA batteries for $36 ($7 off)</ins></a></p> \n<p>Earlier this year I replaced all the disposable batteries in my home with rechargeable ones — including some of these from Tenergy — and it's been one of the best decisions I've made in a while. Not only do Tenergy's Premium Pro NiMH batteries have some of most capacity in their class at 2,800mAh for the AAs or 1,100mAh for AAAs, they're also rated for up to 1,200 recharges. That means compared to traditional disposable batteries, these cells will pay for themselves after less than a dozen charging cycles. And with them being on sale for just $36 during Prime Day, if you're the type of gamer that is constantly chewing through batteries to power stuff like Xbox Series S/X controllers or other accessories, this deal represents the kind of savings you can't really afford to miss.</p>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-best-prime-day-gaming-deals-on-video-games-hardware-and-more-to-get-before-the-sale-ends-144228893.html?src=rss	2025-07-11 23:00:35	Sam Rutherford,Kris Holt	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.487671
379	14	Prime Day laptop deals: Save on MacBooks, Windows 11 machines, Chromebooks and others before the sale ends	https://www.engadget.com/deals/prime-day-laptop-deals-save-on-macbooks-windows-11-machines-chromebooks-and-others-before-the-sale-ends-130057009.html?src=rss	<p>If your laptop simply isn’t cutting it anymore, <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-best-amazon-prime-day-deals-for-the-last-day-our-top-picks-on-headphones-tvs-robot-vacuums-and-more-120028336.html">Amazon Prime Day</a> might have arrived just in time. As has been the case for the past few years, laptop deals are abundant this Prime Day, bringing discounts to MacBooks, Windows laptops, Chromebooks and more. But we wouldn’t blame you if you didn’t know how to figure out if that laptop you’re eyeing actually has a good discount for Prime Day, or if the deal is stale.</p> \n<p>That’s where Engadget can help. We’ve poured over the Prime Day laptop deals available this year to pick out the best ones you can get across all kinds of computers. If you’re super picky about the specs you want in a new laptop, we always recommend going straight to the manufacturer so you can configure the machine exactly to your needs. But if you’re willing to work with premade models, Prime Day deals could help you save some cash on your next laptop. Just be sure to make your selection quickly, because we expect most of these deals to end tonight when Prime Day is officially over.</p> <span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>\n<h2 id="jump-link-prime-day-laptop-deals-macbooks">Prime Day laptop deals: MacBooks</h2> \n<p>Apple’s latest laptops are the MacBook Air M4 and the MacBook Pro M4, but the M3-powered machines are still available and great values when you can get them at steep discounts. But for the most future-proof options, we recommend going with the M4 MacBooks. Amazon actually has decent MacBook deals throughout the year, most of the time on the base configurations of any given model. In a welcomed update, Apple recently made all base models of the MacBook Air M4 have 16GB of RAM by default (which is the same as you’ll find on the base-level Pros).</p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DZDBWM5B&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=MacBook+Air+%2815-inch%2C+M4%2C+16GB+RAM%2C+256GB+SSD%29+for+%241%2C049+%28%24150+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRFpEQldNNUIvcmVmPWZzX2FfbWJ0Ml91czI_&amp;signature=AQAAAX4SZkPTDLXjZZ1P3AXhQ3t4DS_yhyCWJH7i2_QOBpJB&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0DZDBWM5B%2Fref%3Dfs_a_mbt2_us2">MacBook Air (15-inch, M4, 16GB RAM, 256GB SSD) for $1,049 ($150 off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DLHB9X2G&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=MacBook+Air+%2815-inch%2C+M3%2C+24GB+RAM%2C+512GB+SSD%29+for+%241%2C299+%2824+percent+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRExIQjlYMkc_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTNlOGZjN2QtZDFlZC00ZDBjLWJlNjUtMmE5YTY0NzJhMDJlIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRExIQjlYMkciLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZthAR4OArGJXezmSqgd50eoh1jrUTyTllp84bWHsK-Y&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0DLHB9X2G">MacBook Air (15-inch, M3, 24GB RAM, 512GB SSD) for $1,299 (24 percent off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DLHBYRPS&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=MacBook+Pro+%2814-inch%2C+M4%2C+16GB+RAM%2C+512GB+SSD%29+for+%241%2C429+%2811+percent+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRExIQllSUFMvcmVmPWZzX2FfbWJ0Ml91czE_&amp;signature=AQAAAQM8oSt0TJp2H3GcRQYKPKB_qtjm8GqhDw65h3-8dFOf&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0DLHBYRPS%2Fref%3Dfs_a_mbt2_us1">MacBook Pro (14-inch, M4, 16GB RAM, 512GB SSD) for $1,429 (11 percent off)</a></p></li> \n</ul> \n<h2 id="jump-link-prime-day-laptop-deals-windows-laptops">Prime day laptop deals: Windows laptops</h2> \n<p>You’ve got a lot of variety to choose from when it comes to Windows laptops, and that can be a blessing or a curse. We recommend looking for a laptop from a reputable brand (i.e. Microsoft, Dell, Acer, Lenovo and others like them), and one that can handle daily work or play pressures. That means at least 8GB of RAM and 245GB of SSD storage, plus the latest Intel or AMD CPUs. If you’re looking for a new gaming laptop, you’ll need a bit more power and a dedicated graphics card to boot. Now is a good time to consider upgrading as well since Windows 10 will be sunset in October this year and <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=67071605-d4df-494e-8d9c-c9c236b8bb38&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Microsoft&amp;linkText=Microsoft+has+recommended&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5taWNyb3NvZnQuY29tL2VuLXVzL3dpbmRvd3MvZW5kLW9mLXN1cHBvcnQ_cj0xIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhM2U4ZmM3ZC1kMWVkLTRkMGMtYmU2NS0yYTlhNjQ3MmEwMmUiLCJvcmlnaW5hbFVybCI6Imh0dHBzOi8vd3d3Lm1pY3Jvc29mdC5jb20vZW4tdXMvd2luZG93cy9lbmQtb2Ytc3VwcG9ydD9yPTEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAaL6x7jj6-2QyIGdihwrpcGtG37n9NHdZ66bEREAVUdq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fwindows%2Fend-of-support%3Fr%3D1">Microsoft has recommended</a> users upgrade to newer Windows 11 laptops.</p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DSLNMY6M&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+Galaxy+Book5+360+%28Windows+11%2C+Copilot%2B%2C+15.6-inch%2C+Intel+Core+Ultra+7%2C+16GB+RAM%2C+512GB+SSD%29+for+%241%2C050+%2822+percent+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NBTVNVTkctQ29tcHV0ZXItVG91Y2hzY3JlZW4tU3BlYWtlcnMtTlA3NTBRSEEtS0ExVVMvZHAvQjBEU0xOTVk2TS8_&amp;signature=AQAAAaSy9X-ChXk9k1wBI6JVlClsyhGLMXg4nf5ICeWZ4rmd&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSAMSUNG-Computer-Touchscreen-Speakers-NP750QHA-KA1US%2Fdp%2FB0DSLNMY6M%2F">Samsung Galaxy Book5 360 (Windows 11, Copilot+, 15.6-inch, Intel Core Ultra 7, 16GB RAM, 512GB SSD) for $1,050 (22 percent off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0F7HJJN7Z&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Lenovo+V15+G2+laptop+%28Windows+11+Pro%2C+15.6-inch%2C+Intel+Celeron+N4500%2C+32GB+RAM%2C+1TB+SSD%29+for+%24429+%2828+percent+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAVO8Neep4Bp9ofey7Yi-annZezZG6abv4lFzZOECdc6_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLenovo-Computer-Business-Student-Processor%2Fdp%2FB0F7HJJN7Z">Lenovo V15 G2 laptop (Windows 11 Pro, 15.6-inch, Intel Celeron N4500, 32GB RAM, 1TB SSD) for $429 (28 percent off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0F2KT481H&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Dell+Inspiron+3520+laptop+%28Windows+11%2C+15.6-inch%2C+Intel+Core+i5%2C+8GB+RAM%2C+512GB+SSD%29+for+%24350+%2822+percent+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0RlbGwtSW5zcGlyb24tMzUyMC1MYXB0b3AtMTUtNi1pbmNoL2RwL0IwRjJLVDQ4MUg_&amp;signature=AQAAAXv1XILihM_elS90vbInyMRa-2JUHnUKpu279Ilnsv28&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDell-Inspiron-3520-Laptop-15-6-inch%2Fdp%2FB0F2KT481H">Dell Inspiron 3520 laptop (Windows 11, 15.6-inch, Intel Core i5, 8GB RAM, 512GB SSD) for $350 (22 percent off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CP8D4SM2&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Acer+Nitro+V+gaming+laptop+%28Windows+11%2C+15.6-inch%2C+Intel+Core+i5%2C+RTX+4050%2C+8GB+RAM%2C+512GB+SSD%29+for+%24650+%28%24150+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdxiaWN-rsvrKEnAjXwW_9T79lfZ-OOpf6qXsCP28Eb4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fi5-13420H-Processor-GeForce-Display-ANV15-51-51H9%2Fdp%2FB0CP8D4SM2">Acer Nitro V gaming laptop (Windows 11, 15.6-inch, Intel Core i5, RTX 4050, 8GB RAM, 512GB SSD) for $650 ($150 off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CRCYJ8YV&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=ASUS+ROG+Strix+G16+gaming+laptop+%28Windows+11%2C+Intel+Core+i9%2C+RTX+4060%2C+16GB+RAM%2C+1TB+SSD%29+for+%241%2C595+%28%24105+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfMev2GKFwzrw16JU90pak49V3OW8flDAeETz9Cg4tOU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FASUS-Gaming-Laptop-Nebula-Display%2Fdp%2FB0CRCYJ8YV%2F">ASUS ROG Strix G16 gaming laptop (Windows 11, Intel Core i9, RTX 4060, 16GB RAM, 1TB SSD) for $1,595 ($105 off)</a></p></li> \n</ul> \n<h2 id="jump-link-prime-day-laptop-deals-chromebooks">Prime Day laptop deals: Chromebooks</h2> \n<p>Most Chromebooks start off pretty affordable, so that just means you can get them for even less during an event like Prime Day. If you’re a Chrome OS lover, it’s also a decent time to check out sales on premium Chromebooks, which can usually cost $500 or more. In general, we recommend looking for at least 4 to 8GB of RAM and at least 128GB of SDD storage in a Chromebook that you plan on using as your daily driver.</p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<ul> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0F4GD28JM&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=HP+Chromebook+14+%2814-inch%2C+Intel+N100%2C+8GB+RAM%2C+128GB+UFS%29+for+%24295+%2811+percent+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0hQLUNocm9tZWJvb2stUHJvY2Vzc29yLUNoYWxrYm9hcmQtMTRhLW5mMDA5OW5yL2RwL0IwRjRHRDI4Sk0_&amp;signature=AQAAAWIWm9UmGsxfvVOwUWWc3dvwZTMW1ArDydghRLw1Gqi6&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHP-Chromebook-Processor-Chalkboard-14a-nf0099nr%2Fdp%2FB0F4GD28JM">HP Chromebook 14 (14-inch, Intel N100, 8GB RAM, 128GB UFS) for $295 (11 percent off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B07YMGQYP6&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Google+Pixelbook+Go+%2813-inch%2C+Intel+Core+M3%2C+8GB+RAM%2C+64GB+storage%29+for+%24319+%2851+percent+off%29&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYcA8Ed59DNd6151pHIiB1lyVZRwj51VHORdR3QmcrAP&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixelbook-Chromebook-64GB-Black%2Fdp%2FB07YMGQYP6%2F">Google Pixelbook Go (13-inch, Intel Core M3, 8GB RAM, 64GB storage) for $319 (51 percent off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CX28KX1N&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Acer+Chromebook+Plus+514+%2814-inch%2C+Intel+Core+i3%2C+8GB+RAM%2C+128GB+SSD%29+for+%24323+%2819+percent+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2FjZXItQ2hyb21lYm9vay1QbHVzLUxhcHRvcC1Hb29nbGUvZHAvQjBDWDI4S1gxTi8_&amp;signature=AQAAAcCbiQD1RiFWZBFoRiK_5dCrz3buPhH8EZ2PbPfRTKMI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Facer-Chromebook-Plus-Laptop-Google%2Fdp%2FB0CX28KX1N%2F">Acer Chromebook Plus 514 (14-inch, Intel Core i3, 8GB RAM, 128GB SSD) for $323 (19 percent off)</a></p></li> \n <li><p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D16P1MFJ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=a3e8fc7d-d1ed-4d0c-be65-2a9a6472a02e&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=HP+Chromebook+Plus+x360+%2814-inch%2C+Intel+Core+i3%2C+8GB+RAM%2C+128GB+UFS%29+for+%24329+%2845+percent+off%29&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0hQLUNocm9tZWJvb2stVG91Y2hzY3JlZW4tR3JhcGhpY3MtMTRiLWNkMDAxMG5yL2RwL0IwRDE2UDFNRko_&amp;signature=AQAAAQeY7PNFq8hh6fx3L8f7fUZru5qLphR7RvZAWHdWBO7D&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FHP-Chromebook-Touchscreen-Graphics-14b-cd0010nr%2Fdp%2FB0D16P1MFJ">HP Chromebook Plus x360 (14-inch, Intel Core i3, 8GB RAM, 128GB UFS) for $329 (45 percent off)</a></p></li> \n</ul>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/deals/prime-day-laptop-deals-save-on-macbooks-windows-11-machines-chromebooks-and-others-before-the-sale-ends-130057009.html?src=rss	2025-07-11 22:30:37	Valentina Palladino	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.490266
385	14	Amazon Prime Day 2025: The deals that the Engadget team spent our hard-earned money on	https://www.engadget.com/deals/amazon-prime-day-2025-the-deals-that-the-engadget-team-spent-our-hard-earned-money-on-154509453.html?src=rss	<p>Amazon's <a href="https://www.engadget.com/the-best-prime-day-apple-deals-on-airpods-ipads-macbooks-and-more-for-day-three-of-amazons-sale-150005681.html">Prime Day</a> is in full swing, and now that two full days have passed, some of us have gotten past our decision paralysis and checked out our online shopping carts. It's no surprise that the Engadget team consists of people who are fans of tech (and non-tech) products, and we also love a good deal. As we've put together <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/amazon-prime-day-has-the-best-deals-on-laptops-this-week-save-on-macbooks-windows-11-machines-chromebooks-and-others-130057842.html">roundups</a> and news stories about the <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-best-prime-day-deals-on-amazon-devices-save-up-to-68-percent-on-kindle-ereaders-echo-speakers-and-more-082012114.html">best things to buy this week</a>, we've also been tempted by the savings. Here's a list of what several of our team members bought, not only to share our lives with you but to also show you some of the deals we deemed good enough to spend our own money on.&nbsp;</p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<p><strong><em>(Ed. note: Igor Bonifacic saved a whopping $2 on this guitar tuner, but it was worth it to him. I'll let him explain.)</em></strong></p> <span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>\n<p>In Canada, the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=D%27Addario+tuner&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZxH3EZkLeLKQuthe9w7WVmE2hdbSWc19MU2LOqlisle&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.ca%2FDAddario-Guitar-Tuner-Headstock-Acoustic%2Fdp%2FB01IBI88R4%2F">D'Addario tuner</a> I ended up buying is normally a little more expensive at $20 CAD, but I figured there was a chance it would go on sale for Prime Day. So I set up a Camelcamelcamel alert, and on the morning of July 8 I got an email from the website saying it was… $2 off. Not the greatest discount, but hey, in such an expensive hobby, every dollar counts, right?</p> \n<p>This past spring, I picked up the guitar for the first time in about 15 years. How it happened doesn't matter. What does matter is that now I play everyday, and I've been asking myself why did I ever stop in the first place. I feel more creative, my eyes feel healthier from less screen time and I'm better now than I ever was as a teenager.</p> \n<p>As I've gotten back into the hobby, I've slowly been buying all the little accessories that can make it easier to maintain your guitar. With Prime Day around the corner, I set my sights on a headstock tuner. These little gadgets weren't around when I first started learning the instrument, but let me tell you they're great.</p> \n<p>Like the name suggests, you attach one to the headstock of your guitar. It then allows you to tune the instrument by measuring the vibrations produced by the strings. While you could just as easily use an app like <a href="https://yousician.com/guitartuna">GuitarTuna</a> to do the same, clip-on tuners aren't affected by ambient noise, making the entire tuning process fast and easy. Best of all, they're cheap. In the US, you can spend as little as $15 to buy the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B01IBI88R4&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=model+I+purchased+for+Prime+Day&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUtOrFkZMMcVnYk3p5JaczvsJ1lcEBOinFn0orqNb7tF&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDAddario-Accessories-Eclipse-Headstock-Tuner%2Fdp%2FB01IBI88R4%2Fref%3Dsr_1_2_sspa">model I purchased for Prime Day</a>. — <strong><em>Igor Bonifacic, senior reporter</em></strong></p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<p>Without even trying, I've become a devotee of <a href="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/smartphones/how-to-use-your-iphone-as-a-webcam-with-your-mac-164248242.html">Apple's Continuity Camera</a> over the last few years. I think with my laptop and monitor setup, it's just always made more sense to use my iPhone as a camera rather than buying some kind of USB-C docking station or giving up another port on my computer. Unfortunately, I also find having my phone within arm's reach while I'm writing to be pretty distracting. Taking advantage of a Prime Day deal on a dedicated webcam this year is my solution.</p> \n<p>I purchased an off-white <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B09QW1WVRD&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Logitech+Brio+500&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAW8TEXcA2C91zkqpElfDNBXJGLl58v5G9HrEPhwYOV-_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLogitech-Correction-Auto-Framing-Reduction-Microsoft%2Fdp%2FB09QW1WVRD">Logitech Brio 500</a>, which normally costs $130, but is $50 off for Prime Day through Amazon or <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=9d8b417f-05d3-461d-8465-21e1a10e527d&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Logitech&amp;linkText=Logitech&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbSTpl5zvT_7F0tLjNwxb2kE-XMYfWs1QA2wCzzruj1n&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.logitech.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fp%2Fbrio-500-webcam.960-001432">Logitech</a>. It's a kind of a long, tube-shaped 1080p webcam, so not the sleekest or best option out there, but it has the basics I need, like a manual shutter and auto-framing, and critically, it matches my Logitech mouse. If, like me, you can't stand the idea of paying over $100 for a webcam, I think it's a pretty appealing option at $80. — <strong><em>Ian Carlos Campbell, contributing writer</em></strong></p> \n<p></p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<p>I recently discovered that as all my gear transitioned to USB-C, I no longer had any compatible thumb drives. Rather than buy an adapter dongle that I would inevitably lose, I figured it would be smart to have a new thumb drive that could handle both USB-C and USB-3. The discount on the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B06XC1WGQR&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=SanDisk+drive&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NhbkRpc2stMjU2R0ItVWx0cmEtRHJpdmUtVHlwZS1DL2RwL0IwNlhDMVdHUVI_&amp;signature=AQAAATsaZemJHjz58GEAmU66k_tIe2F8adqoozOSKe8fZcDK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSanDisk-256GB-Ultra-Drive-Type-C%2Fdp%2FB06XC1WGQR">SanDisk drive</a> I bought wasn't huge, but Prime Day seemed like a good time to save a few bucks on a practical purchase. — <strong><em>Anna Washenko, contributing reporter</em></strong></p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<p>Even though it wasn't on sale this week, I pre-ordered a re-issue for the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CSGZCTLS&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Studio+Series+version+of+Blaster&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZSuV4gH25Y5UGa5eHQ6ym_43ZgSfjXjd3wwWafwwBMC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FTransformers-Voyager-Universe-Soundwave-Converting%2Fdp%2FB0CSGZCTLS%2F">Studio Series version of Blaster</a> from Amazon because he is one of my favorite Transformers of all time. And then I added <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CY8C34ZF&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Soundwave&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWww4FSzNXs8c9Rnifejkv1tBciGPMM_Q7li_x_G5ww0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FTransformers-Generations-Voyager-Figurine-Autobot%2Fdp%2FB0CY8C34ZF%2Fref%3Dsr_1_1">Soundwave</a> to my shipment because he's another one of my top 10 favorite bots and you can't really have one without the other. And then I found a small deal on <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DK7Z3SG6&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Heatwave&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeic-cAx6Mrk8rDNvWXmSIfNG7FAvUa55ecg0INZHbO-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FTransformers-Primes-Voyager-Heatwave-Converting%2Fdp%2FB0DK7Z3SG6%2Fref%3Dsr_1_1">Heatwave</a>, so we picked that up too as a way to save a couple bucks on a present for my son's birthday next month.</p> \n<p>It's a bit weird to say that as an adult I'm still this fascinated by plastic toys, but sometimes it feels like we're living through a golden age for Transformer figures despite the awful movies we've been subjected to over the last decade and a half (aside from Transformers One). As bad as the Bayverse films are, there's still a rich history of shows and toys and I've had a blast diving back into all of that with my kid. — <strong><em>Sam Rutherford, senior reviewer</em></strong></p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<p>I made a very short, focused list of three things to buy on Prime Day — a <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BDMTZYXZ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Nori+Press&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAetSJ--qBEiXqJdy2ed5wOHHvqrMV37q_MMH8fNZSHbV&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FNori-Press-Travel-Steam-Iron%2Fdp%2FB0BDMTZYXZ">Nori Press</a>, a walking pad and the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1aa15d48-ca00-4b80-bd7a-a85bf2cf4507&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Tonies&amp;linkText=Ms.+Rachel+Tonie+toy&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3VzLnRvbmllcy5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlYjIwOWE2Zi0yMDJlLTQ1ZWYtYWUzZC02YTdkOGI0MTg0ZDMiLCJvcmlnaW5hbFVybCI6Imh0dHBzOi8vdXMudG9uaWVzLmNvbS8ifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAcnOf1ElLLUINVrlerl-VEdSOCd5SLbVg8VzxFq9-VNq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fus.tonies.com%2F">Ms. Rachel Tonie toy</a> for the kids in my life. But when I was looking through our roundup of the best deals this week, the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0DZ75TN5F&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=discounted+entry-level+iPad&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATwtmxV9SsCcVNNDIxbPmvOtfI3XZ6H-Ru4Nc50WSvYI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FApple-iPad-11-inch-Display-All-Day%2Fdp%2FB0DZ75TN5F">discounted entry-level iPad</a> caught my eye.&nbsp;</p> \n<p>My dad had been asking me repeatedly for weeks about an iPad for watching videos and movies while him and my mom were traveling, and I wasn't able to give them an answer as I was weighing a lot of concerns. What is the best operating system for them? Do they need something released recently, or could they save some money on an older model?&nbsp;</p> \n<p>Seeing this <a href="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/tablets/ipad-2025-with-a16-review-no-apple-intelligence-no-problem-132641539.html">current-generation iPad</a> on sale prompted me to just buy it for them. It simplifies things as my dad uses an iPhone and is familiar with iPadOS, and apps like YouTube and Netflix would satisfy their desires to download videos to watch offline. Saving $70 on what is a very solid device felt like a great deal, but more importantly it earned me points with my family. — <strong><em>Cherlynn Low, managing editor</em></strong></p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<p>Like I mentioned earlier, the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0BDMTZYXZ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Nori+Press&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAetSJ--qBEiXqJdy2ed5wOHHvqrMV37q_MMH8fNZSHbV&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FNori-Press-Travel-Steam-Iron%2Fdp%2FB0BDMTZYXZ">Nori Press</a> was on my list of things to buy when on sale this week. In fact, the Nori Press was on <a href="https://www.engadget.com/best-tech-gifts-on-our-editors-wishlists-130043069.html">my holiday wishlist last year</a>. Alas, none of my friends or family got it for me, so I decided finally to buy one myself. The ice-cubes-in-the-dryer method just didn't cut it anymore.&nbsp;</p> \n<p>Nori frequently has sales that put the iron, which usually retails for $120, at $100. When I saw that the Prime Day discount dropped the price down to about $90, I figured it was time to stop procrastinating. I haven't received the iron yet, but I'm certainly excited to wear crisply collared shirts and neatly pressed dresses soon. — <strong><em>Cherlynn Low, managing editor</em></strong></p> \n<h2 id="jump-link-what-were-still-considering">What we're still considering</h2> \n<p>As Prime Day goes on till the end of the week, many on the Engadget team are still weighing their decisions. Executive editor John Falcone, for example, hasn't bought <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D8PYWHZR&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=eb209a6f-202e-45ef-ae3d-6a7d8b4184d3&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Anker%27s+UFO+3-device+charger&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUFZkv8w-swc5HtSIkHj6L_EoDPqsb7UNgKHZuws2i-s&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAnker-Compatible-Wireless-Certified-Foldable%2Fdp%2FB0D8PYWHZR%2F">Anker's UFO 3-device charger</a>, but says he wishes he did. I'll update this post if he does, because he will save almost 30 percent on it.</p> \n<p>Not all our purchases have been through Amazon, either. Editor-in-chief Aaron Souppouris is thinking about buying "a weird camera for too much money not on Amazon." It's a full-spectrum conversion camera, and if and when he does make that purchase, we will be sure to shame him here.</p> \n<p>Finally, senior editor Billy Steele has made arguably the best shopping decision all week, on or <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/walmart-deals-2025-rivals-prime-day-with-sales-up-to-47-percent-off-230146367.html">off Amazon</a>. He bought "three Happy Meals trying to get the cool toys. I got three of the same toy. :("&nbsp;</p> \n<p><strong>Update, July 10 2025, 5:00PM ET:</strong> This story has been updated to add a section on what senior reviewer Sam Rutherford bought.</p> \n<p><strong>Update, July 11 2025, 12:00PM ET:</strong> This story has been updated to add a section on the Nori Press.</p>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/deals/amazon-prime-day-2025-the-deals-that-the-engadget-team-spent-our-hard-earned-money-on-154509453.html?src=rss	2025-07-11 16:00:35	Cherlynn Low	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.496504
386	14	Subnautica studio co-founder says he's suing parent company Krafton	https://www.engadget.com/gaming/subnautica-studio-co-founder-says-hes-suing-parent-company-krafton-153412484.html?src=rss	<p>The <a href="https://www.engadget.com/gaming/subnautica-2s-early-access-release-delayed-to-2026-amid-developer-drama-123042406.html"><ins>drama</ins></a> surrounding the significantly delayed release of <em>Subnautica 2</em> continues with Charlie Cleveland, co-founder and <a href="https://krafton.com/en/news/press/krafton-announces-gaming-industry-veteran-steve-papoutsis-as-new-ceo-of-unknown-worlds/"><ins>former director</ins></a> of Unknown Worlds Entertainment, announcing <a href="https://x.com/Flayra/status/1943467965434974522"><ins>via a post on X</ins></a> that he and unnamed others have filed a lawsuit against<a href="https://www.engadget.com/gaming/pubg-will-get-ai-powered-npcs-220218057.html"> <ins>Krafton</ins></a>, the studio's parent company since 2021.</p>\n<p>Cleveland, along with Ted Gill and Max McGuire, were<a href="https://krafton.com/en/news/press/krafton-announces-gaming-industry-veteran-steve-papoutsis-as-new-ceo-of-unknown-worlds/"> <ins>relieved of their leadership roles</ins></a> at Unknown Worlds last week by Krafton.<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-07-09/krafton-delays-subnautica-2-game-ahead-of-250-million-payout?embedded-checkout=true"> <em><ins>Bloomberg</ins></em><ins> reported</ins></a><em>&nbsp;</em>that they had been effectively &quot;pushed out.&quot; This occurred shortly before Krafton would reportedly owe Unknown Worlds leadership a $250 million bonus for meeting certain goals.</p>\n<span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>The alleged lawsuit follows Krafton's <a href="https://www.engadget.com/gaming/subnautica-2s-early-access-release-delayed-to-2026-amid-developer-drama-123042406.html"><ins>recent statement</ins></a> accusing Cleveland and other studio leadership of &quot;abandoning their responsibilities.&quot; The parent company claims these executives' behavior led to significant delays in <em>Subnautica 2</em> 's early access release, which is now slated for early 2026. Krafton also claimed that approximately 90 percent of the $250 million bonus was already paid out to Cleveland, Gill and McGuire.</p>\n<p>In<a href="https://x.com/Flayra/status/1943467965434974522"> <ins>his post</ins></a>, Cleveland strongly refuted Krafton's claims, asserting that <em>Subnautica 2</em> is in fact &quot;ready for early access&quot; and that any allegations regarding abdication of leadership and financial motivations are false. &quot;Subnautica has been my life’s work and I would never willingly abandon it,&quot; Cleveland wrote.</p>\n<p>He also firmly denied accusations that he and other executives intended to keep the promised $250 million bonus for themselves, saying, &quot;I’m in this industry because I love it, not for riches. Historically we’ve always shared our profits with the team and did the same when we sold the studio. You can be damned sure we’ll continue with the earnout/bonus as well.&quot;</p>\n<p>Details about the lawsuit, including the jurisdiction, named parties or specific causes of action remain unclear. <em>Subnautica 2 </em>is still slated for an early access launch sometime in 2026, though it remains to be seen if this new legal drama will cause further delays.</p>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/gaming/subnautica-studio-co-founder-says-hes-suing-parent-company-krafton-153412484.html?src=rss	2025-07-11 15:34:12	Andre Revilla	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.49774
387	14	Prime Day deals include the Samsung Galaxy Watch 7 for an all-time-low price for the last day	https://www.engadget.com/deals/prime-day-deals-include-the-samsung-galaxy-watch-7-for-an-all-time-low-price-for-the-last-day-110001283.html?src=rss	<p>If you're a Samsung phone user or prefer Android in general, there are some excellent sales on tech accessories to check out for the last day of <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-best-amazon-prime-day-deals-for-the-last-day-our-top-picks-on-headphones-tvs-robot-vacuums-and-more-120028336.html">Prime Day</a>. One of the best ones is on the <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D1YNVD88&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=bd2f873a-d8ee-4d8b-9324-c18037d4191b&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Samsung+Galaxy+Watch+7&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRDFZTlZEODg_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYmQyZjg3M2EtZDhlZS00ZDhiLTkzMjQtYzE4MDM3ZDQxOTFiIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwRDFZTlZEODgiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAX8-JmXqtVh34-XCuZAE-dSP4g3VP6ayS-AtJaHP2XOD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D1YNVD88">Samsung Galaxy Watch 7</a>, which is on sale for only $160 right now. That's a record-low price for this smartwatch.</p> \n<p>This is the company's latest watch and was released back in February, so it's nice to see a massive discount this early in the release cycle. We appreciated the Galaxy Watch 7 <a href="https://www.engadget.com/wearables/samsung-galaxy-watch-7-review-incrementally-better-than-its-predecessoragain-133038627.html">in our official review</a>, calling it a "capable companion for Samsung phones." It features an old-school design that recalls classic timepieces and not modern smart devices.</p> <span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>\n<p>\n </p> \n<p>The performance is zippy, thanks to an upgraded processor, and the storage has doubled when compared to its predecessor. There are also many more sensors when measured against the Galaxy Watch 6. For instance, there are now 13 heart rate sensor LEDs. This leads to the ability to assess more complex health metrics, like sleep apnea detection. All of this is data viewable via the fun and intuitive Samsung Health app.</p> \n<p>We also appreciated that this watch will automatically track workouts when you start, without asking if you're exercising like with the Apple Watch. There are even some AI-assisted tools here that offer light coaching as you workout or engage in physical activities.</p> \n<p>There are a couple of little quirks here. First of all, this watch is primarily for those already tied into Samsung's ecosystem. If you use an iPhone, this might not be the best match. Also, the always-on display is a notorious battery hog. Still, this is a lot of smartwatch for the money.</p>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/deals/prime-day-deals-include-the-samsung-galaxy-watch-7-for-an-all-time-low-price-for-the-last-day-110001283.html?src=rss	2025-07-11 15:28:56	Lawrence Bonk	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.498557
388	14	FBI seize well-known Nintendo Switch game piracy site	https://www.engadget.com/gaming/nintendo/fbi-seize-well-known-nintendo-switch-game-piracy-site-152216405.html?src=rss	<p>One of the most popular sites for Nintendo Switch piracy has been taken down as part of an ongoing FBI investigation. As reported by <a href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-piracy-nsw2u-roms-fbi-hack-emulator-zelda-1851786034"><em><ins>Kotaku</ins></em></a>, Nsw2u was known for hosting Switch ROMs, which users could download to play on a hacked Switch or PC emulator capable of running them.</p>\n<p>At the time of writing, when you enter the site’s URL you’ll see a notice confirming the seizure, which the FBI says is in accordance with a warrant issued by the United States District Court in Georgia. The notice also features a logo for the Fiscal Information and Investigation Service (FIOD), which is a Dutch government agency that investigates financial crimes.</p>\n<span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>Nintendo has been cracking down on piracy of its games for a number of years. Back in 2019, the company <a href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-09-12-nintendo-sues-rom-website.html"><ins>sued</ins></a> the illegal ROM-sharing site RomUniverse, after it became aware it was offering unlimited downloads of new and old Nintendo games for an annual fee. Last year it filed a <a href="https://www.engadget.com/gaming/nintendo/nintendo-is-suing-a-streamer-of-pirated-software-for-millions-of-dollars-150052133.html"><ins>lawsuit</ins></a> against streamer EveryGameGuru who it accused of broadcasting footage of pirated — and in many cases unreleased — Switch games, as well as providing access to illegal ROMs. In March of 2024 the makers of popular Switch emulator Yuzu paid $2.4 million to <a href="https://www.engadget.com/makers-of-switch-emulator-yuzu-quickly-settle-with-nintendo-for-24-million-203204698.html"><ins>settle</ins></a> charges filed by Nintendo.</p>\n<p>Nintendo’s latest <a href="https://www.engadget.com/gaming/nintendo/nintendo-grants-itself-the-power-to-brick-switches-with-pirated-games-162129077.html"><ins>anti-piracy move</ins></a> was inserting a clause in an updated version of the <a href="https://en-americas-support.nintendo.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/48058/~/nintendo-switch%3A-user-agreement"><ins>Nintendo Switch User Agreement</ins></a> that effectively enables it to brick your Switch if it runs illegal emulators or pirated games. This revised agreement came into effect just ahead of the <a href="https://www.engadget.com/gaming/you-can-finally-buy-the-nintendo-switch-2-on-amazon-but-dont-expect-a-prime-day-deal-195558235.html"><ins>Switch 2</ins></a> launch on June 5.</p>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/gaming/nintendo/fbi-seize-well-known-nintendo-switch-game-piracy-site-152216405.html?src=rss	2025-07-11 15:22:16	Matt Tate	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.499367
