399	14	The Ring Pan-Tilt Indoor Cam is still in stock and down to $40 for Prime Day	https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-ring-pan-tilt-indoor-cam-is-still-in-stock-and-down-to-40-for-prime-day-123513813.html?src=rss	<p>Ring's indoor camera that has a motorized base to give you a 360-degree view is cheaper than ever in a <a href="https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-best-amazon-prime-day-deals-for-the-last-day-our-top-picks-on-headphones-tvs-robot-vacuums-and-more-120028336.html">Prime Day</a> deal. The <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0CRMD7JGD&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=db469f38-2528-44bd-8af9-9572876c6abf&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=Pan-Tilt+Indoor+Cam&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ1JNRDdKR0Q_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZGI0NjlmMzgtMjUyOC00NGJkLThhZjktOTU3Mjg3NmM2YWJmIiwib3JpZ2luYWxVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQ1JNRDdKR0QiLCJkeW5hbWljQ2VudHJhbFRyYWNraW5nSWQiOnRydWUsInNpdGVJZCI6InVzLWVuZ2FkZ2V0IiwicGFnZUlkIjoiMXAtYXV0b2xpbmsiLCJmZWF0dXJlSWQiOiJ0ZXh0LWxpbmsifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdfRgpJhFMafDPXHnrl2Tj0m6EB6pq9XxRXEqegmCrcb&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0CRMD7JGD">Pan-Tilt Indoor Cam</a> normally goes for $80, but it's dropped to just $40 for the Amazon savings event. That's even lower than the previous all-time low price of $50 that we've seen during other sales. The Pan-Tilt camera comes in five colors: Black, Blush, Charcoal, Starlight and White.</p> \n<p>\n </p> \n<p>Ring <a href="https://www.engadget.com/rings-new-indoor-camera-lets-you-pan-and-tilt-for-a-better-view-130047398.html">introduced the Pan-Tilt Indoor Cam</a> in 2024. It can spin a full 360 degrees on its base, and tilts up and down with a tilt range of 169 degrees. That makes it especially helpful for keeping tabs on pets and other goings-on in the home. It offers live views in addition to 24/7 recording, and supports two-way talk for when you want to check-in with a family member. The Pan-Tilt Cam also offers HD color video day and night.</p> <span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>\n<p>The camera has a physical shutter as well, for when you want to be sure it's not watching. Sliding this will cover the camera, and Ring says it'll also disable the audio and video feeds. Setup should be easy with the Ring app, but if you aren't already in the Ring ecosystem, you'll need a subscription to use this camera. Ring offers <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b50ccd99-4c85-48e0-a2ed-9c2b9b65422b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=db469f38-2528-44bd-8af9-9572876c6abf&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Ring&amp;linkText=three+subscription+options&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3JpbmcuY29tL3BsYW5zIy9jb21wYXJlLXBsYW5zIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJkYjQ2OWYzOC0yNTI4LTQ0YmQtOGFmOS05NTcyODc2YzZhYmYiLCJvcmlnaW5hbFVybCI6Imh0dHBzOi8vcmluZy5jb20vcGxhbnMjL2NvbXBhcmUtcGxhbnMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdp2gOriOLyhvO2mVhlsr4UYQPLiQSiiuIpdCPt8JRTo&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fring.com%2Fplans%23%2Fcompare-plans">three subscription options</a> at $4.99, $9.99 and $19.99 per month.</p>This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/deals/the-ring-pan-tilt-indoor-cam-is-still-in-stock-and-down-to-40-for-prime-day-123513813.html?src=rss	2025-07-11 12:31:26	Cheyenne MacDonald	f	2025-07-14 05:01:46.509985
