ef="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/tablets/ipad-air-m3-review-a-modest-update-thats-still-easy-to-recommend-130045196.html">review score of 89</a> upon its debut this March. When you pair it with accessories like a keyboard folio and mouse, it becomes a true productivity machine — though those add-ons make it a pricey package. Good thing iPads are on sale for Prime Day. This $120 discount represents the lowest price we've seen. Also at <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=5e0bed65-d2f8-4b34-9b8f-955218c0e37a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=5c2b9c33-9a87-45ff-b978-e41b8f7a90a2&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Best+Buy&amp;linkText=Best+Buy&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWbZ848KqJqP9Su1sZ0VsawpA8g0Rt0pknHiCFV-Ntxk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fsite%2Fapple-13-inch-ipad-air-m3-chip-built-for-apple-intelligence-wi-fi-128gb-space-gray%2F6578297.p%3FskuId%3D6578297">Best Buy</a>.&nbsp;</p> \n<p><a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D3J9XDMQ&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;contentUuid=5c2b9c33-9a87-45ff-b978-e41b8f7a90a2&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;linkText=iPad+Pro+%28M4%2C+11-inch%29+for+%24915+%28%2485+off%29%3A&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWpcfA-PWqD2DKwJftrJo2ahfaQrF-enYo7s7wTyQzCp&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0D3J9XDMQ%2F"><strong>iPad Pro (M4, 11-inch) for $915 ($85 off):</strong></a> The <a href="https://www.engadget.com/mobile/tablets/best-ipads-how-to-pick-the-best-apple-tablet-for-you-150054066.html">most powerful iPad</a> is the iPad Pro, and it’s the one to get if you’re even toying with the idea of using your new slab as a laptop replacement. Both the 11- and <a class="rapid-with-clickid" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;itemId=amazon_B0D3J98W75&amp;siteId=us